INSERT INTO `job` VALUES (1,'לחברת השקעות מובילה – רילוקיישן לקפריסין','לחברת השקעות מובילה – המשקיעה בין היתר בחברות היי טק לרילוקיישן לקפריסין\nדרוש/ה: אנליסט/ית השקעות לתחום ההיי טק\n\n\nהתפקיד כולל:\nניתוחי השקעות חדשות – בדיקות כדאיות ונאותות\n\nניתוחי השקעות קיימות – ניתוחי תזרים, תקציב מול בפועל, kpi’s ועוד.\n\nדרישות:\nרו”ח/ כלכלן/ית\n\nניסיון בתחום הייטק/ פינטק/ קרנות – מה ביג 4\n\nאו\n\nניסיון במחלקה כלכלית במשרד\n\nאפשרות גם לנסיון של תפקיד אחד אחרי משרד .\n\nאנגלית ואקסל ברמה גבוהה','2020-07-24',1),(2,'Marketing Analyst','Traffic Point is an online commerce company with the goal of streamlining the consumer decision-making process, and connecting customers with industry-leading brands. The networks we create help shoppers make smarter decisions about the products they want to buy.\n\nWe are seeking a highly motivated Marketing Analyst to join our growing team in Tel Aviv.\n\n\n\nThe successful candidate will be required to:\n\nCreate, analyze and optimize PPC campaigns on a daily basis. Responsibilities will include carrying out marketing research, analyzing marketing performance data, setting up mainly Search campaigns & handling high budgets in highly competitive markets.\n\nSkills & Experience:\n\nExcellent analytical skills & passion for numbers\nAbility to work on several projects simultaneously and independently\nUniversity degree in fields such as economic, mathematics etc. / B.Sc. graduated magna cum laude / high psychometric.\nScience, business or analytical academic background an advantage.\nExcellent analytical skills.\nLanguage: English - Native or high level of proficiency\nAdditional non-English Language - advantage\nResults driven, ambitious & hard worker.\nOnline marketing experience - an advantage.','2020-07-16',2),(3,'Devops Engineer','We are looking for a talented DevOps Engineer with Kubernetes expertise to join our growing team\nAutomat-IT is a software, consulting and integration company, specializing in end to end DevOps Automations. As a member of the DevOps Team, you will be joining a small, collaborative team responsible for a wide array of systems for our customers.\n\nJob Requirements & Qualifications:\nStrong understanding of Docker managers (Kubernetes, SWARM) - must.\nExtensive knowledge of Linux server environments.\nGood understanding and knowledge of automation/configuration management systems (Puppet, Chef, or Ansible is an advantage).\nKnowledge and experience with Continuous Integration/Deployment best practices and servers (Jenkins).\nWorking with version control systems (Git).\nExperience with Artifacts management (Artifactory/Nexus - an advantage).\nWorking with AWS, Azure, GCP - an advantage.\n\nSend your resume to hr@automat-it.com','2020-07-13',3),(4,'Mobile Team Leader','AnyVision, is the worlds leading designer and developer of face, body and object recognition platforms, first founded in 2015 in order to solve real-world problems.\nWe are a fast growing company that is seeking a talented and experienced person to join our A(i) Mobile team.\nOur Mobile team consists of talented Android and IOS developers with highly developing skills, who can be our go-to-guy for all architecture and innovation related.\nYou are:\nA great team player who is passioned and aptitude about research and utilize new top technologies. Love to train, educate and mentor new team members. You have an ability to work in a constantly changing, fast-paced, deadline driven environment.\nYou will:\nManage a team of developers while still coding approx 30% HO.\nBe responsible for implementing new technologies with the team.\nLead architecture solutions design along with the team and the Development.\nTeam members training, mentoring & on-boarding.\nPerforming Code Reviews.\nProduce quality products that meet high quality, stability and performance standards.\nWork closely with the research team in implementing new features.\nTackle problems and find creative ways to solve them.\nWorking with customers.\n\n\nRequirements:\nYou previously worked in a similar role as a Mobile Team Leader - for at least 2-3 years.\nYou have knowledge with Kotlin, Swift, MVVM / MPV / MVC architecture.\nYou have experience working with remote data via REST and JSON.\nYou have experience in Git, Jira, Agile.\nYou have knowledge and experience working and releasing SDK to customers.\nYou have knowledge in OOD and Design patterns.\n\nIt would also be nice if:\nYou have experience in JavaScript, python\nYou have experience in Flutter\nYou have experience in React Native\nYou hold a Bachelors Degree in Science, Programming or Engineering.\nBenefits\nNo traffic & absolutely no parking problems.\nFull board\": Breakfasts and lunch budget.\nGet the opportunity to work in a fast-paced global startup with an enterprise-level client portfolio.\nDog-friendly office.\n\n\nLocation::\nHolon, Israel','2020-07-27',4),(5,'Product Manager in AI','#AI startup #serial_entrepreneurs. Join a team of professionals, working in big data, signal analytics, and machine learning.\n#Flex_hours\n\n* B.Sc in Computer Sciences or similar.\n* 5 years of proven experience as a product manager in commercial software companies.\n* Strong business and technical orientation.\n\nTake an active part in building the main company’s product:\n-Working with the R&D and QA\n-Working closely with multiple departments\n-Responsible for communicating the business requirements to the engineering teams.\n-Identify internal needs and opportunities through data, interviews, and research.\n-Proven ability to manage a complete product life-cycle','2020-07-16',5),(6,'Part Time Bookkeeping Assistant, Contract - Whisk','This role is part of our Finance team within Samsung NEXT organization\n\nAbout Samsung NEXT\n\nSamsung NEXT champions builders and founders inventing a more purposeful future. We attract, develop, and celebrate diverse talent with world-class capacity to transform ideas into realities at scale. Our team exclusively works with software and services startups that have the potential to complement Samsung\'s market-leading consumer hardware. Our innovation model blends the best of both worlds: the agility of a startup with the scale of one of the world\'s leading consumer electronics companies.\n\nFounded in 2012, Samsung NEXT has four key functions in the global software ecosystem:\nVentures: invests in startups that have the potential to scale by leveraging the Samsung ecosystem\nPartnerships: creates partnerships with innovative companies to enrich Samsung products and services\nM&A: acquires game-changing companies to bring their products and services to consumers worldwide\nProduct: designs and builds software experiences to transform the way we work and live\nThis is a newly created part-time (20 hours/week) contractor role supporting the CFO of Whisk, a UK-based SaaS startup, acquired by Samsung NEXT in March 2019. The successful candidate will assume operational responsibility for key payables/receivables processes, with opportunities for extended scope as the business scales. The preferred location for this exciting opportunity is at the Samsung NEXT office in Tel Aviv, Israel, where the CFO is located.\n\nCore Responsibilities:\n\nPayables:\nInvoice control and storage.\nInvoice payment (incl. batch payments).\nReconciliation in general ledger (Xero) in conjunction with external accounting support in the UK.\nAdministrator for contracts and renewable subscriptions => provide Whisk CFO with visibility.\nContractors reimbursement payments\nReceivables:\nInvoice customers in line with the sales pipeline.\nDebt collection.\nReconciliation in general ledger (Xero) in conjunction with external accounting support in the UK.\nCash Management:\nManage the company bank account.\nManage credit card accounts.\nOther:\n\nSystems Administration:\nExpensify\nTravelPerk\nFuture systems\nSupport data requests for external audits.\nAd hoc projects.\nSkills/Attributes:\n\nTechnical:\nExperience/Qualification: Minimum 2-3 years\' of accounting experience or an accounting degree. Strong understanding of debits and credits. Bookkeeping Level 1-2 a strong advantage.\nTools: Advanced knowledge of MS Excel, Google Suite (Docs, Sheets) a must.\nSystems: Demonstrable experience of working with a general ledger (ideally cloud based, e.g. Xero, QuickBooks).\nLanguages: Fluent English, Hebrew essential. Additional languages are beneficial.\nSpecialist: Knowledge of UK regulatory environment (e.g. VAT laws) a significant advantage, but not a must.\nCommunication: Strong communication skills, with an ability to communicate across a global, distributed organization (prior exposure to tools such as Telegram and Slack beneficial).\nPersonal Traits:\nMindset: High attention to detail and able to perform under pressure.\nCustomer Centricity: Internal & external\nIntegrity: Ability to manage sensitive information with care.\nA passion for technology.\nWhat do we offer?\nAutonomy: An entrepreneurial culture, backed by the most senior leadership of a highly successful, multinational tech company.\nColleagues: Supportive and highly skilled colleagues across a range of international locations.\nFlat structures and exposure to senior leadership.\nAt Samsung NEXT, we hold the steadfast belief that diversity and inclusion is essential to realize our mission and is a must-have for us to do our best work. We are proud to be an Equal Employment Opportunity employer and do not discriminate on the basis of race, color, ancestry, national origin, citizenship, religion, sex, sexual orientation, gender identity, age, ability, marital status, veteran status, or any other legally protected status.\n\nWe will ensure that individuals with disabilities are provided reasonable accommodation to participate in the job application or interview process, to perform essential job functions, and to receive other benefits and privileges of employment. Please contact us to request accommodation.\n\n#LI-EO1','2020-07-21',6),(7,'Development Infrastructure Lead','AnyVision is a world leading team of scientists and engineers that creates AI for the Real World. With deployments and clients spanning the globe, we are recognised as leaders in the fields of Face Recognition, Object Recognition, Object Detection, and Visual Target Tracking.\nAnyVision is dedicated to providing a diverse and flexible work environment so that we can recruit and retain the best talent.\nYou are:\nResponsible for designing, developing, installing, configuring and maintaining an Anyvision Development Infrastructure which powers the testing pipelines of our company, providing cutting edge resource orchestration and testing capabilities to our researchers and developers across the globe.\nYou will:\nWork with senior management on the Anyvision Development Infrastructure roadmap.\nWork with researchers and developers to understand their development needs .\nWork with Python, Docker, Redis, docker-compose, Kubernetes, AWS and libvirt /qemu.\nCreate Makefiles and Shell scripts to aid in the spin up and tear down of infrastructure services.\nWork with researchers and developers to help them with integration.\nContinuously strive to improve the performance, stability and featureset of the Anyvision Development Infrastructure.\nEnsure the Anyvision Development Infrastructure development team is operating at its potential.\n\n\nRequirements:\nA minimum of 3 years software development experience (Preferably in Python)\nAbility to communicate freely in English\nExperience working with a public cloud. Ideally AWS\nExperience working with hypervisors. (KVM)\nProven experience designing and implementing software and cloud architectures\nSolid understanding of Linux (Admin Level) and comfortable working with networks\nProven experience maintaining and configuring scripts (Makefiles/Shell/Python)\nVery good understanding of docker and docker-compose\nProven experience working with Kubernetes\nIt would also be nice if:\nExperience with LibVirt and Qemu\nExperience with Python\nExperience working with PyTest, async and websockets\nExperience with Redis, SQL Databases, Kafka, Mongo\nExperience with Docker BuildKit\nExperience working with GPUs\nSolid understanding of GIT and best practices surrounding SDLC\nBenefits:\nNo traffic & absolutely no parking problems.\nFull board\": Breakfasts and lunch budget.\nGet the opportunity to work in a fast-paced global startup with an enterprise-level client portfolio.\nDog-friendly office.\n\n\nLocation::\nHolon, Israel','2020-07-21',4),(8,'Senior Enterprise Architect','ClickDimensions was founded in 2010 to make Microsoft technology work for marketers so they can\n\ncreate great experiences. Our marketing automation platform is natively integrated with Dynamics\n\n365, eliminating the need for complex implementations and constantly syncing systems while\n\ndelivering unparalleled access to CRM data for better segmentation, hyper-personalization and\n\nmarketing success.\n\nWith essential marketing tools like email marketing, campaign automation, web intelligence, surveys,\n\nweb forms and landing pages, social marketing and more, ClickDimensions helps organizations that\n\nuse Microsoft Dynamics 365 attract more leads, close more sales and more effectively engage\n\ncustomers.\n\nJob Description\n\nThe Senior Enterprise Architect analyzes, translates, and composes both technical and nontechnical\n\ninformation into clearly readable documents, design artifacts, and deployable reference\n\nstacks (i.e., code) that are used by technical and non-technical personnel. The scope and type of\n\nwork products will range widely, and artifacts will be used at multiple levels of the organization.\n\nAlign IT architecture technology strategy and frameworks to enable the company\'s business strategy\n\nand goals, by providing guidance and building consensus among and across stakeholders.\nTranslate strategies into target architectures and roadmaps; articulate and evangelize\ndesign/architectural roadmaps across the organization.\nDefine current enterprise architecture and identify issues or disruptive technologies within it.\nRefine and/or redesign and develop reference architecture to meet the organization’s changing\nbusiness requirements.\nImplement new Enterprise Architecture in a large enterprise environment and drive adoption with\nan understanding of cybersecurity best practices.\nEvangelize and articulate cloud, SOA, integration, microservices and other architecture\nprinciples, benefits and technical solutions to senior level business and technical audiences.\nLead and mentor and highly talented and technical staff in Enterprise Architecture principles;\ncollaborate with staff to provide consensus-based enterprise solutions that are scalable and\n\nadaptable.\nAlign IT strategy and planning with agency goals.\nDrive efficiency improvements to reduce cost and improve information flows.\nLead the development of current \"as is\" and future \"to be\" architecture documentation and drive\nstrategic plan for transition.\nParticipate in architecture definition for Cloud Initiatives utilizing industry best practices and\ntechnologies.\nProvide hands-on designs, prototypes, and implementations incorporating architecture &\nsoftware engineering best practices.\nLearn and analyze current industry technology trends, best practices and patterns for Cloud\nDevelopment.\nEvaluate tools, technologies and POCs related to Cloud technologies/solutions.\nRole Essentials\nBS Degree in Information Technology, Computer Science or related degree.\nExperience designing, integrating, and managing complex infrastructure and application\nsolutions 10+ years in the software engineering and IT Architecture & Solution Delivery\nExperience in architecture with Azure Cloud Platform and others including: (AWS, GCP)\nExperience working with IT and Security leadership to articulate security and or compliance\nstrategies and plans.\nUnderstands and can articulate the technical and business merits and value of public cloud\ncomputing.\nPassionate, persuasive, articulate cloud professional capable of quickly establishing interest and\ncredibility in how to design, deploy and operate cloud-based architectures.\nAbility to work independently and willingness to learn new technologies and methodologies at\nthe pace of public cloud service providers.\nStrong understanding across cloud and infrastructure components (server, storage, network,\ndata) and cloud abstracted platform services to deliver end to end cloud architectures and\n\ndesigns with full-stack awareness.\nHands-on experience architecting complex solutions with Azure Data Services, Data Lakes,\nDatabricks, and Data Factory\nDemonstrated knowledge and/or understanding of Azure-based tools and services that support\ndata storage, e.g. Azure SQL, Blob and Structured and Non-Structured Storage, Cosmos DB\nHands-on Software development experience using Azure native solutions like Azure Functions,\nDevOps CI/CD etc.\nProgramming experience in .NET, C#, Python and other languages.\nHandling of data ingress and egress from the cloud (Azure, AWS).\nEstimating cloud costs and identifying associated cost-control mechanisms.\nStrong written, verbal and white board skills.\nStrong practical experience administering and scripting automation for Linux or Windows\nsystems (e.g., Python, Ruby, bash, PowerShell).\nExperience with Continuous Integration & Delivery (CI/CD) Role Desirables\nWorking knowledge of Cloud technologies such as: (Kubernetes, Docker, Terraform, Packer,\nCloudFormation)\nRelevant Industry certifications such as AWS Certified Solutions Architect, Microsoft Azure\nCertified Solutions Architect Cloud Platform, or Google Professional Cloud Architect strongly\n\npreferred\nExperience in cross functional leading team applying all elements of Technical Consulting','2020-07-28',8),(9,'Senior Full Stack Developer','Panoply, democratizing data worldwide, is growing and looking for a 2 Senior Full-Stack Developer to join our Platform Team.\nAs a Senior Developer, you will lead the development of complex features, from design to deployment, of a high-performance and scalable Platform. You will join a small team of brilliant engineers, where technical debates and creative problem solving are everyday practice.\nFew words about us:\nPanoply is set out to democratize big data, eliminating the time and effort SMBs spend gathering the data they need for business intelligence. We make it easy and fun to digest hundreds of different data sources, in real-time and petabyte-scale. The developers at Panoply are working on building a cutting-edge platform that can absorb massive amounts of data, in minutes, and make it simple and intuitive for our users to load, transform and explore their data.\nThe challenges are enormous, we require our developers to push the boundaries of creative thinking with top-notch technical expertise.\nFew words about you:\nWe are looking for an Engineer to take a new feature and be responsible for its development from requirements through testing to deployment. Making the required research, getting familiar with our BaseCode in a way that will enable you to understand the dependencies, and think of all the edge cases.\nTeam Work is one of our core values, and our Senior Developers are natural Leaders & Mentors. Willing and eager to assist and guide Junior Developers as well as Senior Developers. Tech Debates and Brainstorming is an everyday practice, and we are having a weekly meeting discussing last week’s retrospect and next week\'s development tasks.\nIn a team where everybody is doing everything, each person finds his own expertise, the ideal Senior Developer who will join our team, has gained expertise either in CI/CD processes or Front-End development.\nOur Stack: GO, Nodejs, Python. AWS, Azure, Kubernetes, Docker.\nWho you are:\nPassionate about technology & coding\nDriving to be the best\nGreat at figuring things out\nGetting things done.\nMust have:\nWe don\'t really care in what language you code, we care about your code quality: if your code is Maintainable & Readable, and you think of Performance & Scalability while coding - Ping us :)\nAt least 5 years of experience in developing infrastructure and/or product core\nComprehensive expertise in Object-Oriented Design, Software Architecture, Algorithms & Data Structures.\nExperience with Linux and Web-related technologies, AWS, Database Design.\nWill “wow!” us with:\nExpertise in UX/UI and Front-End development, developing in React, OR in DevOps\nExperience in massive-scale data processing, using Redshift, Hadoop, Spark, EMR, Google BigQuery.\nExperience or contribution to high-profile open-source projects.','2020-07-28',9),(10,'Tech Lead','YesChef is a venture-backed, early-stage tech and media startup. We\'re building our team from the ground up and seeking out top talent to build the world\'s premier platform for food education - a Netflix for cooking!\n\nJob description\n\nWe\'re seeking to hire a deeply experienced tech lead to join and build our rapidly growing R&D team. We\'re looking for someone with a career\'s worth of of knowledge, insight and passion to help us build the future of food.\n\nMinimum requirements for our Senior Web Developer position:\n5+ years experience in web development, including JS, Node, Linux, Git a must\nProduct-focused thinker & Autodidact\nExperience with cloud environments\nKnowledge in React\nKnowledge in Video streaming, Docker, ElasticSearch, Firebase, Mongo DB - an advantage\nComputer Science (or similar) degree\nBonus points:\nStartup: experience working in an early-stage tech startup here in Israel\nLove for cooking and food - a huge advantage *\n\nAbout YesChef:\n\nWe\'re building the world\'s premier platform for food education - a Netflix for Cooking. YesChef will boast a library of exclusive video classes taught by the world\'s greatest chefs. We\'ve built a rich, interactive digital platform and user experience, and we\'re out to become the leading international brand in home cooking, taught by the most authoritative chefs on the planet.\n\nYesChef is on a mission to let anyone learn from the world\'s best chefs, and become a chef at home. We\'re working with world-class chefs to develop immersive video classes that take you on a journey around the world, by combining cinematic storytelling with hands-on teaching to deliver a completely new kind of educational experience for home cooking.\n\nhttps://yeschef.me','2020-07-27',10),(11,'Product Designer','We are looking for a creative and passionate Product Designer to join our product team in Tel Aviv.\nAs a Product Designer, you will translate high-level requirements into clean visual solutions to ensure great user experience for our customers.\nOur ideal candidate is focused on customer & user centric design, a team player with a desire to learn and grow and is comfortable working in a highly complex technological environment.\nIf you are passionate about designing products and a desire to create simple user experiences without compromising on aesthetics, this is the right challenge for you.\n\n\nRequirements:\nAt least one year of hands-on experience as a UX / UI Designer\nExcellent visual design abilities\nMastery of all Adobe CC software\nGood personal skills: team player, independent, organized, open-minded, and flexible with strong time management skills\nAnalytic thinking with attention to details and problem-solving mindset\nStrong portfolio\nAdvantages:\nVisual Communication degree from a top art collage\nProficiency in HTML, CSS, and JavaScript\n\nWhen applying, please provide a link to your portfolio.\n\n\nResponsibilities:\nDesign complex user interfaces optimized for simplicity and performance.\nImprove existing user interface designs and flows.\nMaintain and extend our product style guide.\nCollaborate with product managers to design user flows and prototype mockups.\nExecute all visual design stages from the concept phase, through wireframes and complete design to development.\nWork closely with R&D to ensure that the implementation meets the design.','2020-07-21',11),(12,'Platform Team Leader','Panoply, democratizing data worldwide, developing a SaaS platform where you can store, sync, and access all your business data,\nis growing and recruiting a Platform/Data Engine Team.\nFew words about us:\nPanoply is set out to democratize big data, eliminating the time and effort SMBs spend gathering the data they need for business intelligence. We make it easy and fun to digest hundreds of different data sources, in real-time and petabyte-scale. The developers at Panoply are working on building a cutting-edge platform that can absorb massive amounts of data, in minutes, and make it simple and intuitive for our users to load, transform and explore their data.\nThe challenges are enormous, we require our developers to push the boundaries of creative thinking with top-notch technical expertise.\nThe Role:\nAs a Team Leader, your mission is to break our monolith to micro-services, and creating a fast, accurate, and effective ingestion process, while leading and mentoring a team of 5 backend developers.\nOur Stack: GO, Nodejs. Kubernetes, AWS & Azure\nResponsibilities:\nE2E ownership for delivering your product: plan, design, develop, track status, test, and deliver.\nDeveloping a fast, effective, and stable data ingestion process.\nWork closely with Product, Research Team & Support in order to achieve a clear and accurate understanding of the complex product and changing client requirements.\nEstablish successful development processes, guiding the team to produce high quality, performant code, while still coding 30% of the time\nResponsible for Data Security and SOC compliance\nA Mentor, growing a team of excellent developers\n\nWhat you bring to the team:\n1.5 - 2 years of experience as a Team Leader (5-10 developers), preferably from startup companies.\n4-6 years of experience in Software Development, preferably in Go and Nodejs\nExperience with large scale production systems, cloud architecture, preferably in the big data industry.\nA Doer, with excellent time management and delivery abilities\nGreat leadership and mentoring skills\nPlease send your CV to ayelet@panoply.io','2020-07-06',9),(13,'Fullstack Javascript Engineer','Totango is looking for a Full Stack Javascript engineer to join our start-up environment & innovative web application team.\n\nRequired Skills:\nJavascript professional\nSkilled in any Client-side MVC framework (Ember, Angular, React, Backbone etc.).\nNode.js hands-on experience.\nBsc. in computer science / information technology or relevant industry experience in building rich Javascript applications\nSelf learning capabilities\nTeam Player.\nNice to have: AWS, ElasticSearch, Redis, Mobile development experience.\n\nMission: Help us build and improve our amazing rich enterprise-grade web application.\n\nWhy work with us?\n\nTotango is a fast growing start-up building an ambitious cloud application. Youll have the opportunity to learn cutting edge technologies and make an impact.\n\nTotango leads the exciting new field of Customer Success. We help business pro-actively support their existing clients and reduce churn.\n\nFun company events and high standard welfare facilities.\n\nGood work/life balance.\n\nGreat location near Sarona and Hashalom train station in Tel-Aviv.\n\nPowered by JazzHR','2020-07-28',13),(14,'HR Data Analyst - Part-time Role for Students','What\'s the job?\n\n\nironSource is looking for a talented Analyst for our HR team, part time (3 days a week)\nResponsibilities\nPull data from a variety of internal systems (recruiting system, employee management system) in order to outline problems, opportunities draw conclusions and make recommendations for future consideration\nAnalyze people data frequently, draw conclusions and make recommendations for future consideration\nProvide in-depth insights/reports on employee trend/issues including turnover & headcount report to support critical HR actions and recruitment processes.\nBuild dashboards & reports, and define key metrics, while also monitoring the integrity and validity of the data reported.\nAnalyze data from internal hr surveys (employee engagement, managers evaluation, performance review) and gather insights.\nApply your expertise in research to make recommendations on HR decisions (processes, policies, operations, etc)\nPartner with HR business leaders to identify and clarify critical issues.\nCommunicate statistical analyses and results: tell the story of the data to stakeholders in order to equip them to make informed decisions and plan for the future.\nProduce ad-hoc reports and analysis to identify trends on our workforce\n\nRequirements\nBA/MA student studying economics, psychology and business management.\nExcellent analytical skills – Must\nExpert in MS Excel\nAbility to create detailed spreadsheets, charts, and presentations\nStrong research abilities\nNice to have – familiarity with HR operations including hiring, payroll, and employee benefits\nWork experience as an HR Analyst or similar role- a big advantage\nExperience using Human Resources Management Systems- a big advantage','2020-07-16',17),(15,'Software Architect','As a Software Architect at Next-Insurance, you will lead complex software projects and affect the System\'s Architecture simultaneously bottom-up, and top-down. You are clearly hands-on and enjoy tackling the more challenging pieces of software. At the same time, you understand the organization - how it operates, and how to operate it. We\'re big fans of Lean Startup - so Architects have the additional challenge of how to promote MVPs and Lean Experimental Architecture, while also caring and thinking on the System in the long-term. You will work closely with engineering teams on various projects, with Product Managers, Insurance Experts, BI, and any other party that would be relevant. You will gain and maintain a deep understanding of the System and the Business - allowing you to find leverages of making a real impact. You will have opportunities to mentor engineers and managers, and assist in building a healthy and advanced Engineering Culture.\n\n\nDesired Skills and Experience:\nPassionate about delivering remarkable software to impact the lives of real people\nExperience building large scale, complex Web-Systems.\nExperience working in a startup / SaaS product - a clear advantage.\nExperience working in a mature organization - an advantage.\nHands-on, extensive experience writing code and tests.\nAbility to find a good and balanced solution for complex problems :)\nA true believer in simplicity over cleverness.\nAbility to simplify complex ideas and communicate them clearly to various audiences.\nExperience with Lean-Startup, TDD, TCR, DDD, managing complex business logic - an advantage.\nAbility to drive initiatives that are not code-oriented, e.g. forming new engineering processes, from inception to running reliability without the initiator.\nAbility to be hands-off, eyes-on, and affect initiatives not owning.\nA believer in team-work and a positive atmosphere','2020-07-23',18),(16,'Data Analyst','About us\nTailor Brands is one of the few B2C companies in the country. Each month, we help 500k new users start and grow their dream business. Through tools like our automated logo maker, branding and design studio, domain registrar, website builder, etc. we’re committed to making starting a business affordable and accessible to everyone.\nWhat we’re looking for\nA resourceful individual to build models to predict performance and customer behavior\nAnalysis and optimization of our marketing efforts in the digital world\nDevelopment of reports, dashboards, KPIs and metrics\nMonitoring of business KPIs and product metrics to alert about changes\nSomeone to come up with new ways to use our data to create value for our users\nSomeone to bring insights and suggestions to Product Managers, Marketing, Customer Success, Finance and Management by conducting deep analysis and research\nAnalysis of raw data according to complicated business questions\nApply if you have\n2+ years of experience with advanced skills in SQL, data analysis and visualization\nB.A./B.Sc. in a relevant field\nUnderstanding of statistical models\nExperience working with BI/Analytics tools (e.g. Tableau, Looker, Periscope, Qlik etc.)\nExcellent teamwork skills and the ability to work autonomously\nNice-To-Haves\nExperience analyzing online consumer product performance\nExperience working with online advertising data\nFamiliarity and/or implementation experience with tracking and data collection techniques\nStatistical analysis experience (e.g. R, Python, MATLAB)','2020-07-13',21),(17,'Data Analyst','Ever been shopping online and felt that you were misled to another site? Have you ever felt that your personal information was misused or shared without your consent?\nThe Namogoo platform gives back control of the customers journey by uncovering and preventing all the hidden factors interacting with eCommerce visitors and ensuring their experience is exactly as they intended.\nNamogoo is trusted by more than 100 leading brands, including Asics, Argos, Samsonite, Office Depot, and Teva to provide a safe and healthy journey for their millions of customers.\nNamogoo has been announced by Dun & Bradstreet as the Best Israeli Startup to Work For in 2019!\nNamogoo is hiring a Data Analyst to analyse complex data sets, define and measure KPIs, build and maintain reporting and dashboards and provide insights to support decision-making processes.\n\n\nAbout You:\n2 + years full-time experience as a Data Analyst (post-degree) -MUST\nBA/B.Sc. in industrial/information systems engineering, computer science, statistics or equivalent\nExperience in analyzing and visualizing large-scale datasets\nHigh proficiency in SQL\nExperience in creating ETLs\nPhyton experience- advantage\n\n\nWhat You\'ll Do:\nAnalyze internal and external data sources to reach actionable recommendations for business decisions.\nDesign and create ETLs, reports and dashboards that will provide insights about the product and business performance.\nBuild data-based tools and models for performance monitoring and optimization.\nYoull own a problem end-to-end and use your knowledge and creativity to answer business problems using real data.\nCreate real value from data and communicate with different departments\n\n\nOur Culture:\nSince the company was founded in 2014, we have established good relationships with customers from all over the world and realized a win-win result. Our company and all the staff are committed to providing better value and services to fulfill the needs of each and every customer.\nWe persist in the value of Collaboration, Excellence, Trust and Passion and Customer First all the time. That is our momentum of going forward and the key to success. When it comes to our success, it is all about people, people, people!','2020-07-03',22),(18,'Flexible, Work from Home Opportunity - Web Search Evaluator','At Appen, we work with 8 out of the top 10 global technology companies in the world to improve and optimize their products for users worldwide, including social media platforms, search engines, voice recognition systems, and eCommerce sites. The world of tech is moving fast, and since our founding in 1996 we rose to the challenge by becoming a publicly listed company and by building an international team that works in over 130 countries and in more than 180 languages.\n\nDo you like searching for information on the web, and wonder why you see the results you do? If so, we are looking for new members of our Web Search Evaluator team. As an evaluator, you perform basic tasks online such as providing feedback on search results, advertisements and web page content. Your inpu