y taking ownership and delivering results.\n3 or more years of security experience in one or more of these critical areas: network security, engineering, operations.\nUnderstand security concepts in AWS cloud and familiarity with available AWS security tools, such as Inspector, GuardDuty, Config, CloudWatch, etc.\nFamiliar with log management and security analytics tools, including open source tools such as ELK, Greylog, etc.\nExperience with integrating security in the CI/CD pipeline (running unit tests, running security tools, managing secrets using Vault) using configuration management and automation tools such as Jenkins, Ansible, Terraform, etc.\nGood understanding of computer networking, routing, and protocols.\nGood understanding of information security architecture, mitigation of threats, and compensating controls.','2020-07-22',18),(48,'Logistics Coordinator','NICE is looking for a Logistics Coordinator with proven experience in matrix environment.\n\nJob includes :\nManage level of raw material and Finish Goods inventory\nProduction planning and logistics operations\nManage production schedule and deliverables meeting On-Time-Delivery (OTD)\nAnalysis and resolution of short-term material shortages to meet the schedule\nMonitor data integrity – database parameters, delivery dates, etc.\nDevelop and implement monitoring tools\nImport/export including parcel deliveries\nJob Requirements:\nBachelor\'s degree\n5-10 years of proven experience in production planning, operation management with CM/EMS\nHigh proficiency of MS Excel – mandatory\nERP Oracle experience – advantage\nSelf-motivated, self-starter, energetic, assertive\nAbility to work in a dynamic environment\nAbility to manage and prioritize multiple projects and meet specific goals and deadlines\nStrong interpersonal and leadership skills, ability to lead without formal authority\nHigh level command of English, spoken and written','2020-07-28',62),(54,'Business Planning Manager','Be a part of a revoluti