re, where everyone’s contribution is respected; collaborate with some of the world’s best people and feel like you belong.\n•Pursue your ambitions and develop your skills with a global business – our staggering size and scale provides endless opportunities to progress.\n•Take pride in delivering our promise to society: to improve the lives of a billion smokers.','2020-07-28',29),(55,'Lead Data Scientist','People\'s relationship with food is complicated and we’ve built a platform that simplifies it. Creators of the FoodPrint™, Nutrino uncovers the invisible connections between people and food to empower better nutritional decisions for better health outcomes. Whether it’s finding the foods that love you back, or finding the foods that balance your blood glucose, Nutrino (acquired by Medtronic), is revolutionizing the world of diabetes management.\n\nPassionate, curious and inquisitive about Data and eager to lead a team of professional’s? raise your hand if that’s you.\nWe are currently seeking a Data Scientist Lead to for our team.\n\nWhat does the job require?\n· Ph.D./M.Sc. in math, physics, engineering, computer science or an equivalent science degree\n· 4+ years of experience in data scientist / algorithm development positions\n· Proficiency in Machine Learning, Deep Learning, NLP, Image Recognition, Statistical Models, Control Algorithms. Must have exceptional skills in at least one of them\n· Experience in leading a complex data science problem from ideation to production (or complex and vast academic works)\n· Ability to professionally direct a highly skilled team of data scientists, manage the Data Science roadmap and lead research for future products\n· Strong interpersonal skills and ability to successfully collaborate with talented and opinionated peers (Product, Dev, Quality, etc.) as part of the Nutrino’s team leaders’ group\n\nAdvantages:\n· Track record of leading high performing data science teams\n· Hands on experience in working on a medical/biolog