or customer POC projects, helping enterprise customers utilize their data with Iguazio\'s groundbreaking platform.\n\nYou can expect to:\nDevelop data-science and feature engineering modules on top of iguazio and other open-source frameworks (MLRun, Kubeflow, SKlearn, TensorFlow, PyTorch, Dask, Nuclio etc.)\nBuild end to end demos, POCs and ML pipelines to support new and existing customers who are trying to productize their ML/AI initiatives\nParticipate in research and technology innovation to develop more efficient and automated ways to handle ML/DL workloads at scale\nParticipate in new product/feature definitions\nWork mostly with Python on Kubernetes environment\nThe ideal candidate will have the following:\n3-5 years of experience as a data scientist / data engineer\nExperience writing code in Python and using Python data-science frameworks\nProficiency with a deep learning framework such as TensorFlow or Keras\nBSc in Mathematics, Physics, Computer Science, or another related field\nExperience with building solutions with the Big Data tools and frameworks such as Jupyter Notebook, Spark, Hadoop, Cassandra, NoSQL, etc. – an advantage\nDesign and develop NLP applications and products- an advantage\nAbility to work with external clients together with great communication skills\nAbility to quickly learn new technologies, frameworks, and algorithms\nVery good English, written and verbal','2020-07-20',106),(75,'Data Scientist','CropX Technologies, an exciting start-up (40 employees) located in Poleg is looking for an excellent and experienced Data Scientist to join our awesome team.\n\nAs a Data Scientist, you will build and implement statistical & machine learning models and tools as well as deep analysis to drive insight out of data and find patterns that will help improve our products.\n\nYou will have amazing opportunity to join our excellent team and bring your passion to make a real impact on the way technology works in agriculture.\n\nWe are seeking brilliant, and enthusiastic people who demonstrated excellence across their careers to join our team!\n\nWe believe that every employee in the company can and should make an impact every day, and we empower them to do so. If you are self-motivated, like to take initiative, passionate to solve complex challenges and are a great team player you will love working with us!\n\nYou will be responsible for the following:\nApplying machine learning techniques, doing statistical analysis, and building high quality prediction systems integrated with our products\nResearch and develop innovative approaches and algorithms to extract insights from our data\nPresenting information using data visualization techniques\nWork with stakeholders throughout the organization to identify opportunities for leveraging company data to drive business solutions.\nBuild predictive models and machine-learning algorithms\nRequirements\nProven experience as a Data Scientist\nMaster’s or PhD in Statistics, Mathematics, Computer Science or another quantitative field\nExperienced with using statistical computer languages (R, Python, SLQ, etc.) to manipulate data and draw insights from large data sets.\nExperienced with a variety of machine learning techniques (clustering, decision tree learning, artificial neural networks, etc.) and their real-world advantages/drawbacks.\nExperienced with advanced statistical techniques and concepts (regression, properties of distributions, statistical tests and proper usage, etc.) and experience with applications.\nKnowledge of distributed data/computing tools: Map/Reduce, Hadoop, Hive, Spark, Gurobi, MySQL, etc.\nExcellent communication and presentation skills','2020-07-06',110),(76,'Data Scientist','Being a world leading group in the animal intelligence, we are looking for a data scientist that will help us to discover insights from the vast amounts of data our systems collect.\nIn this role you will utilize data mining techniques, doing statistical analysis, and building prediction models for the purpose of surfacing insights related to livestock and companion animal behavior.\nWe are looking for a highly analytical person, proficient in data analysis, math and statistics, and would like to work with our animal research scientists to achieve better understanding of the animals we monitor.\n\n\nRequirements:\n• B.Sc. or higher in bio-medicine, statistics, applied mathematics, or related discipline\n• 2+ years of experience as a Data Scientist\n• Good applied statistics skills, such as distributions, statistical testing, regression, etc.\n• Strong Theoretical knowledge of Collaborative Filtering, k-Means, Spectral clustering\n• Linear-Algebra - a must (LS, PCA, SVD)\n• Knowledge of SQL and Python; familiarity with Matlab is an asset\n• Strong programming skills\n• Self-learner\n• Team player','2020-07-23',111),(77,'Data scientist','Web Intelligence team is looking for a Data Scientist to join the team and take an important role in the teams current domains Building PayPals Web based solutions leveraging websites crawl data, external APIs data etc. Work closely with cross functional teams on Web related products which would allow global data science teams to use Web data effectively for various business use cases such as fraud, credit, marketing etc.\nAbout PayPals Data Science Team\nAs a Data Scientists in PayPals Global Data Science organization, you will have an impact on PayPals Merchant and Consumer products all around the world. Our data scientists work to better understand our end-users, identify opportunities and improve our products by creating personal and smart experiences. Making use of PayPals endless amount of data, you will leverage your data and machine learning skills, for research and delivery of end-to-end Data Science solutions.\n\nIf you are a Data Scientist with sharp analytical skills and a passion for deriving new insights from unimaginable amounts of data, solving unique challenges, leveraging machine learnin