ur teams.\n\nRequirements\nMaster\'s Degree in Computer Science, Mathematics, Physic, Statistics or equivalent- Must\n2+ years of proven experience working on a data science project.\n2+ years of experience in modeling with Python – Must.\nExperience with machine learning tools and libraries.\nVast experience in Big-Data technologies.\nIntuition about software architecture, design, and performance.\nPassion for technology and constant exploration - must\nAttitude for caring and sharing knowledge - must.\nLove challenges - must.','2020-07-18',117),(79,'לסטארט-אפ צעיר בתל אביב דרוש/ה Data Scientist','מיקום: ת\"א והמרכז\n\nתיאור המשרה:\nדרוש/ה Data Scientist לסטארט-אפ צעיר בתחילת דרכו המקדם חדשנות בענפים רגולטיבים על ידי בניית פלטפורמה המסייעת לארגונים להשתמש בנתונים באופן פנימי לפיתוח ובדיקה ולשיתוף פעולה עם גורמים שלישיים בצורה מאובטחת ותקינה תוך שמירה על פרטיות.\nהמוצר הינו פלטפורמת Data מבוססת Machine Learning, Deep Learning ו-בינה מלאכותית (AI) המאפשרת פיתוח פתרונות מונעי נתונים, החל מחקירה ראשונית ועד לפריסת פתרונות.\nבמסגרת התפקיד, עיסוק במחקר ובפיתוח.\nתנאים טובים, אופציות מאד יפות ומעבר לכך הזדמנות מעולה להשתלב בצוות הCore של המוצר.\n\nדרישות המשרה:\nנסיון של שנתיים כ Data Scientist\nDeep Learning\nתואר שני\nPython\nTensorflow / Pytorch / Keras\nמס\' משרה: 122045','2020-07-23',76),(80,'Data Scientist','ART MEDICAL is a well-funded, medical startup developing cutting-edge technologies for ICU patients. Our smART+™ platform is an intelligent, sensor-based feeding system for critical care patients that aims to prevent life-threatening in-hospital complications such as ventilator-associated pneumonia, malnutrition and acute kidney injury. With the introduction of Nutrition Management 2.0™ to critical care patient scoring systems, the smART+™ platform monitors, analyzes and prevents malnutrition and gastric aspiration in real-time. By providing optimal nutritional care and achieving up to 100% feeding efficiency, the smART+™ platform improves the standard of care and helps ICU patients recover faster.\n\nWe are looking for talented candidates with a previous background in data-oriented positions (data analysis, BI, etc.), this is a great opportunity to join a diverse team working on core company needs.\n\nYou will develop and maintain production grade data science processes, this includes research, analyze and interpret large medical data sets, creating analytical visualizations to help develop a data-driven solution to difficult medical challenges.\n\nWe need you to scale up existing solutions to deal with system loads, optimize existing infrastructures to improve accuracy and runtime and parallelize processes to better utilize computation power.\n\nYou will accomplish this using wide range of technical competencies including: BI, statistics and machine learning, databases, and reporting tools to make sure we are providing the right answers to ART’s business needs.\n\nIdeal candidates for this position will be creative people with an out-of-the-box mindset that have some prior understanding of machine learning models and supporting processes and are great coders.\n\nRequirements:\nAt least 3 years\' experience as a Data Scientist.\nPreferred PhD or Bachelor’s Degree in Mathematics, Physics or Computer Science.\nKnowledge from aspects of the data science life-cycle.\nPractical experience in CUDA, GPU and parallel computing.\nCreative thinker with a proven ability to innovate through data exploration and application of non-trivial solutions.\nExperience in R / Python / Kotlin\nExperience in Neural networking models – an advantage\nExperience with TensorFlow, PyTorch, OpenCV or other machine learning libraries.\nFamiliarity with SQL.\nGood communication skills, ability to clearly explain complex concepts.\nAbility to learn from medical subject matter experts, and implement to search for medical signals in the data.\nAbility to work independently.','2020-07-16',119),(82,'Data Scientist','Intuition Robotics is a VC backed startup