re engineering, machine learning, and statistical algorithms. The candidate should be able to take an idea end-to-end from an early stage of research, through prototyping and up to production-level code.\n\nWhat you\'ll do::\nAnalyze large amounts of time-series data to discover trends and patterns.\nPropose solutions and strategies to meet business challenges.\nResearch and develop statistical learning models and predictive models appropriate for different use cases.\n\nWe\'d love to hear from you if you have::\nHands-on experience in using statistical modeling and machine learning techniques to build predictive models, with at 2+ years of industry work experience.\nHands-on experience with data manipulation and machine learning frameworks in Python, including Numpy, Pandas, and Sklearn.\nBasic knowledge of advanced statistical techniques and machine learning concepts (regression, classification, clustering, etc., ..) and experience with applications.\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills for coordinating across teams.\nStrong analytical skills and learning skills.\nCuriosity and endless desire to learn and improve.\nBSc in Computer Science / Mathematics / Statistics / Physics or any related field (MSc Or/And Ph.D. a plus).','2020-07-21',125),(84,'Data Engineer','Patients need a trusted guide for their healthcare journey and doctors need more time to focus on delivering high-quality care. At Vim, we are using technology to create a value-based healthcare marketplace to increase the quality of care and reduce costs.\n\nWe need people who believe that they can change the way healthcare works. We are looking for experts that want to continue to learn, willing to take smart risks, and are open to possible failure in order to change the status quo.\n\nCome join us!\n\nYour role at Vim as an ETL Engineer:\n\nVim has unique access to health insurance and electronic health record data. Our goal is to use our unique access to this information to help our members and their providers improve the health of the populations we serve. You will be part of the team responsible to organize and transform this data into actionable insights that will help Vim members and providers. In doing so, you will:\nDesign, build and deploy data models and ETLs.\nBuild and maintain the infrastructure for report and dashboard automation.\nCreate and maintain an efficient solution to our highly-sensitive data ecosystem.\nOwn the data exchange between Vim and our external customers.\nCollaborate with other Vim data colleagues to develop internal tools to be able to access our data more readily.\nFuture State: Research and integrate new Big Data tools and frameworks onto our platform.\nWhat would make you a good fit?\nProven experience with ETL design, implementation, and maintenance\nStrong knowledge of SQL\nProven coding experience\nTeam player, self-motivated, hard worker, quick learner, independent and loves challenges\nWillingness to work with our Vim counterparts in San Francisco, CA.\nHigh proficiency of English- verbal and written\nNice to have, but certainly not necessary:\nWorking with AWS or equivalent public Cloud\nExperience working with Ansible\nPython experience- Big plus\nExperience with NoSQL databases\nAbout us: We are headquartered in San Francisco, with R&D in Tel Aviv, and are backed by GreatPoint Ventures, Optum, Sequoia Israel and large BCBS payers. Our customers include health plans and at-risk healthcare systems.','2020-07-24',105),(85,'Data Scientist, Novi','Facebook\'s mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we\'re building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we\'re creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities - we\'re just getting started.For many people around the world, basic financial services are still out of reach: about 1.7 billion adults globally remain unbanked. The cost of that exclusion is significant $25 billion is lost by migrants every year through remittance fees. This is the challenge were hoping to address with Novi, a Facebook subsidiary, whose goal is to provide people everywhere access to safe and affordable financial services through the Libra payment system, which is built on blockchain technology. Our first product will be a digital wallet - Novi - for the Libra network, and it will be available in Messenger, WhatsApp, and as a standalone app.At Novi, you will be working with a talented and dedicated group of people who are passionate about changing the world. Our leadership is experienced and some of the best minds working today in their respective fields.Were looking for Data Scientists to join Novi Customer Care growing team. In this role you will be responsible for driving the Novi Care Experience forward using data analysis and providing insights to empower Novi customers with unparalleled help and education. You will enjoy working with customer care behavioral data sets, a world class team, cutting edge technology, and the ability to see your insights turned into real products and strategy on a regular basis. The perfect candidate will have a background in a quantitative or technical field, experience working with large data sets, data-driven decision making in a customer facing product environment. You are focused on results, a self-starter, and have demonstrated success in using analytics to drive understanding, growth, and success of a product and/or strategy.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nApply your expertise in quantitative analysis, data mining, and the presentation of data to see beyond the numbers and help providing Novi customers with the best customer care experience.\nPartner with cross-functional teams to solve problems, inform solutions creatively with a variety of data, and identify trends and opportunities.\nSet KPIs and goals, design and evaluate experiments, monitor key metrics, understand root causes of changes in metrics.\nUse exploratory analysis to discover new opportunities: understanding ecosystems, user behaviors, and long-term trends.\nInfluence Customer Care teams through clear communication of data-based recommendations, insights, experiment results and state of business.\nMininum Qualifications:\n\nBA/BS in Computer Science, Math, Physics, Engineering, Statistics, or equivalent experience\n3+ years experience doing data science / quantitative analysis, preferably for a web or mobile company\nFluency in SQL\nCore statistical knowledge\nExperience designing and evaluating complex experiments\nPreferred Qualifications:\n\nPython, R or any other scripting language\nBackground of Customer analytics','2020-07-13',127),(86,'Data Scientist','The Data Scientist will be responsible for designing and directing experiments and observational studies to optimize our marketing efforts. This role requires an individual with a strong ability to communicate and collaborate across functional teams, in addition to outstanding analytical and critical thinking skills. The role will have a strong focus on experimental design to support the LifeTouch brand.\n\nResponsibilities:\n\n- Directly impact resource allocation decisions by designing and directing experiments and observational studies\n\n- Partner with the marketing and business strategy teams to define and test hypotheses that answer critical business questions\n\n- Perform deep-dive statistical analysis on large, complex, multi-dimensional datasets.\n\n- Develop and contribute to a base of understanding that allows us to make optimal resource allocation decisions\n\nQualifications:\n\n- Advanced degree (MS, Ph.D.) in quantitative fields, and 2-3 years of experience with a range of techniques, tools, and methods related to data mining and statistical analysis\n\n- Strong ability with a statistical language such as R or SAS, and hands-on experience using a variety of analytical methods\n\n- Experience with or strong working knowledge of experimental design concepts, regardless of industry/discipline\n\n- Hands-on experience with SQL, working knowledge of database design\n\n- Familiarity with internet marketing data collection methods and marketing technology, including search marketing, social marketing, and ad serving platforms\n\n- Creative mind with strong communication and interpersonal skills; talented with simplifying abstract business issues and large amounts of data into actionable analyses; must be able to interact with diverse groups of technical and non-technical people\n\n-Track record of contributing to successful end-to-end analytic solutions (clarifying business objectives and hypotheses, communicating project deliverables and timelines, and informing action based on findings)\n\n- Strong desire to articulate business recommendations based on analytical work','2020-07-17',95),(87,'Data Scientist','Simplex provides an online fraud-free payment processing solution. Simplex enables merchants worldwide to accept diverse payment methods, including credit card deposits and purchases, with zero exposure to chargeback risk.\n\nSimplex\'s AI technology analyzes every transaction using proprietary, fully automated, machine-learning algorithms that eliminate fraud while increasing conversion. By combining advanced payment processing with state-of-the-art fraud prevention technology, Simplex allows Crypto merchants to introduce credit card purchasing to mainstream users worldwide.\n\nWe are looking for a data scientist to join our amazing team.\n\nAs a data scientist at Simplex, you\'ll:\nCreate, build and implement state-of-the-art fraud prevention Machine Learning models to minimize fraud.\nOptimize our product flow to maximize conversion.\nCreate end-to-end solutions from research to a production grade service.\nExtract as much information as you can from external data sources, including identity authentication and social media analysis\nHandle various types of data from multiple sources - some of it tagged, some of it structured, all of it challenging\nInnovate your way to the best possible solution\nMentor our research analysts team with best practices of data science and feature extraction, engineering and ranking\nWhat you need to bring to the table:\nAt least 2 years of relevant work experience as a data scientist.\nExperience in machine learning, statistical tools, applied mathematics, analyzing data.\nExperience with predictive modeling.\nStrong coding background - preferably Python/R.\nA strong desire to learn everything about the company and make a difference.\nBeing creative, open-minded and bottom-up oriented.\nTeam player, motivated, dedicated and fun to be with.','2020-07-28',135),(88,'Data Scientist','Playstudios-IL is anything but a standard games company, in fact - it’s not like any other company you\'ve seen before. Sure, we do build an incredibly entertaining game experiences, and yes, you will see game designers, animators and tech ninjas walking our corridors, but it will feel like living on a rocketship.\n\nWe love data! We use data to guide our every decision and to grow and improve our business. We have an incredible team of Data Scientists, our work is highly sought-after, and our impact on the business is tremendous.\n\nYour role within our team\n\nThe size and complexity of the mobile games environment poses great problems to work on for Data lovers. Our ideal candidate should have one hand on a whiteboard writing equations and the other hand on a keyboard writing code, for those problems simply cannot be solved with human intuition. We are hiring outstanding Data Scientist, who will use innovative statistical and machine learning approaches to generate invaluable insights.\n\nדרישות תפקיד\nLead analytical projects focused on driving customer and revenue growth, working closely with Marketing, Product, and Engineering\nInnovate new modeling and machine learning approaches\nMine data and analytics at user level to gain a better understanding of their funnel and engagement behaviors, including impacts of growth, and conversion rate optimization strategies\nUse exploratory data analysis techniques to identify meaningful relationships, patterns, or trends from complex structured and unstructured datasets\nDevelop tools which provide insights and visualization into channel and funnel performance relative to KPIs, projections, and historical performance. Analyze and determine key insights from business drivers, competitive environment, trends, and operating metrics.\nIdentify impactful business problems and translate them into relevant analyses and actionable insights.\nAnalyze and assist progress of acquisition performance (attribution, paid/organic, etc...), customer lifetime value, and user conversion funnel data by identifying opportunities to improve ROI, engagement and retention.\nRegularly present findings across teams and to senior management to drive optimal decision making\n\nSample project\n\nPredict User Lifetime Value based on user activities to optimize our media sources\nBuild an exploration tool for marketers to optimize ROI and marketing performance\nBuild an AI tool to detect anomalies and spikes in marketing activities such as media spent and product KPIs\n\nworkהגשת מועמדות','2020-07-28',136),(89,'Data Scientist','תיאור המשרה:\nתפקיד המשלב מחקר (יצירה והטמעה של מודלים של Deep Learning ו Big data ) וכתיבת קוד לפרודקשן - תפקיד חלומי!!!\n\nהחברה ממוקמת בתל אביב קו רכבת\n\nדרישות התפקיד:\nתואר שני או דוקטורט במדעי המחשב / סטטיסטיקה / מתמטיקה / פיזיקה- חובה !!!\nהכרות ב- Python / R\nהכרות בעבודה עם BIG DATA.','2020-07-14',140),(90,'Data Scientist','Explorium is a cutting-edge data science company that has recently raised $20m in funding and is rapidly expanding our presence globally.\n\nWe believe in a new paradigm. One where companies can easily and automatically reach the vast world of data and solve their business needs using the most advanced data science and machine learning capabilities. We’re creating a new category as the first company to empower data scientists and business leaders with end-to-end automation of data discovery and feature generation — fueling superior models and driving real business impact.\n\nJob Description:\nWe are looking for a talented Data Scientist with a passion for data and complex problems. You’ll be working with our clients and a team of veteran data scientists to solve tough, real world problems using cutting edge Machine Learning methods.\n\nIf you are someone that thrives in a fast-paced environment where being self-directed, creative and determined are a requirement, we would love for you to join us.\n\nResponsibilities:\nWorking on improving our platform - you will be helping our clients to build predictive models that drive value and revenue.\nCollaborating with product and engineering teams on algorithmic aspects.\nOwn and handle multiple data initiatives and projects.\nResearch, invent and adapt algorithmic solutions for solving data science related challenges.\n\nRequirements:\nRequirements:\nPHD/ M.Sc. in Computer Science/Mathematics/Physics/Engineering or any other relevant field\nAt least 2+ years of hands on experience working as a Data Scientist.\nWorking experience with Python on Machine Learning projects.\nWorking experience with SQL and NoSQL and databases.\nProficiency with Python data stack Numpy, Pandas, Scikit-Learn, XGBoost, CatBoost, LightGBM etc.\nFamiliarity with modern NLP techniques (BERT, GPT-2 etc.), and modern NLP libraries e.g spaCy\nExperience working with TensorFlow 2.0 and PyTorch - Advantage\nExperience working with Spark and proficiency in Scala - Advantage\nSolution orientation and a \"can do\" attitude - with a desire to tackle complex problems.\nA team player with excellent collaboration skills','2020-07-06',141),(91,'Senior Data Scientist','#comp-jl21s07ninlineContent { height: auto; width: 1048px; position: relative; } #comp-jl21s07ninlineContent-gridWrapper { display: flex; pointer-events: none; } #comp-jl21s07ninlineContent-gridContainer { position: static; display: grid; height: auto; width: 100%; min-height: 533px; margin-top: -1px; grid-template-rows: 1fr; grid-template-columns: 100%; } #comp-jnys3y6j { position: relative; margin: 0px 0px 10px 0; left: 0px; grid-area: 1 / 1 / 2 / 2; justify-self: start; align-self: start; } #comp-jl21s07ncenteredContent { position: relative; } #comp-jl21s07ninlineContent-gridContainer > * { pointer-events: auto; } #comp-jl21s07ninlineContent-gridContainer > [id$=\"-rotated-wrapper\"] { pointer-events: none; } #comp-jl21s07ninlineContent-gridContainer > [id$=\"-rotated-wrapper\"] > * { pointer-events: auto; }\n#comp-jnys3y6jinlineContent { height: auto; width: 894px; position: relative; } #comp-jnys3y6jinlineContent-gridWrapper { pointer-events: none; } #comp-jnys3y6jinlineContent-gridContainer { position: static; display: grid; height: auto; width: 100%; min-height: auto; grid-template-rows: min-content min-content min-content min-content min-content min-content min-content 1fr; grid-template-columns: 100%; } #comp-jnys3y7w { position: relative; margin: 0px 0px 33px 0; left: 0px; grid-area: 1 / 1 / 2 / 2; justify-self: start; align-self: start; } #comp-jnys3y8c { position: relative; margin: 0px 0px 23px 0; left: 0px; grid-area: 2 / 1 / 3 / 2; justify-self: start; align-self: start; } #comp-jnys3y8q { position: relative; margin: 0px 0px 55px 0; left: 0px; grid-area: 3 / 1 / 4 / 2; justify-self: start; align-self: start; } #comp-jnys3y94 { position: relative; margin: 0px 0px 26px 0; left: 0px; gr