turing for downstream processing\nDesign accurate and scalable prediction algorithms\nApply advanced\nCollaborate with the engineering team to bring analytical prototypes to production\nGenerate actionable insights for business improvements\n\nAdditional Positions:\nAlgorithm developer\n\nLocation:\nNorthern Israel, Haifa area\n\nCategory:\nSoftware\n\nJob Qualifications:\nBSc degree in Mathematics/ EE /CS/ Information Systems or related field\n\nExperience with at least one of the domains: machine learning, Signal Processing, Neural Networks and statistical predictive modeling.\n\nRelevant engineering background, with OOP (Java/Python/..) coding capabilities\n\nHands on experience with analysis of large data sets under Big Data and distributed computing infrastructures (Hadoop ecosystem)\n\nProficient in Matlab or R or other statistical software package.\n\nCompany Occupation:\nHigh Tech','2020-07-16',150),(98,'Data Scientist','Kenshoo is uniquely positioned as the global leader in digital marketing software solutions, we offer algorithms that bring real value to the worlds top advertisers. Role consists of identifying and defining functionality from conception to delivery, by fully understanding customer requirements, data, \'connecting the dots\', creating an algorithm, and delivering a working algorithm to production.\nRole Description\nAs a Data Scientist on the core data science group, you will be a valuable member of an innovative data science group working on various problems to help and learn from each other to mine insights, find opportunities and \'connect the dots\'.\nData scientists work with business unit product and dev to build and maintain business value by defining, exploring and developing products combining Data Science and Machine Learning at the edge of technology. The data scientists code goes all the way into production with all the responsibility and satisfaction!\n\n\nRequirements:\nBsc or Msc in Computer Science, Mathematics, Statistics, P