oin the AdServing team.\nThe team is responsible for real time serving for the most suitable ad in high traffic and low performance of system in high scale.\nAs a member of our team, you will be responsible for the design and development components with high performance and scale in the advertisement industry\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\nBachelors degree in computer science or equivalent.\nProven work experience as an OO software engineer (5+ years)\nProven work experience with real time, multi threading and large scale systems\nExperience in taking a lead role developing complex software systems that have successfully been delivered\nExperience in technical designs\nExperience in communicating with business teams and management to collect requirements\nExperience with C++ coding\n\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\nExcellent end-to-end system debugging skills\nAWS cloud computing architecture & services\nDevOps experience\nKnowledge with no sql and sql DBs\nTeam player, highly motivated, an independent and fast learner, willing to work in a dynamic and demanding environment','2020-07-09',115),(148,'Software Engineer Graduate - Caesarea - Cisco Silicon One™','What You\'ll Do\n\nYou\'ll develop Core Software technologies at the heart of tomorrow\'s leading infrastructure solutions, tackling the entire range of challenges from user-facing API-s, through high-level algorithms, all the way down to firmware.\n\nThe Leaba core R&D group, now part of Cisco, develops breakthrough next-generation silicon products.\nIf you want to work with amazing people, developing the first iteration of world-class products, join us!\n\nIn this role, you will:\n• Design and develop software driving the world\'s most complex infrastructures\n• Gain intimate knowledge of world-class silicon and programming models\n• Work with architecture and design teams to define the next generation of ASIC products being developed\n\nWho You\'ll Work With\nLeaba semiconductor was acquired by Cisco a few years a