ild the future of driving.\n\nAt Phantom, every day is a unique adventure as we work with the world\'s leading autonomous vehicle companies. Because we collaborate with companies throughout the world, we have the opportunity to develop on many unique vehicles.\n\nAs an early team member, you will be instrumental in defining the foundations of our product and culture.\n\nIf you are determined to take on the world\'s most complex challenges and help build an industry-defining company, this is the opportunity for you.\n\nAs a Full-Stack Software Engineer, you will responsible for architecting, designing, and implementing teleoperation software for remotely driving vehicles. You will be involved with every layer of the technology, including the vehicle-side control system, the server-side communication software, the client-side remote driving application, and the internal tools that make it all a reality.\n\nResponsibilities\nBuild components of a distributed system that enables safe teleoperation of vehicles\nOwn feature implementation end-to-end from technical design to development, testing and release\nBuild & maintain various desktop, embedded and server-side applications\nImprove productivity of the team by contributing to debugging, automation and data tools and pipelines\n\nRequirements\nProficiency with C/C++\nProven distributed systems development track record\nExperience optimizing for speed and scalability\nA user-centric mentality for building products\nStrong Linux background\n\n\nPreferred skills\nJavascript / Node / React\nDocker\nExperience in developing highly robust, safety-centered applications in the fields such as automotive, medical, military, aerospace etc.\nBackground in networking and real-time communication\nKnowledge of video encoding techniques\nComputer Vision','2020-07-28',252),(165,'Software Engineer','Yandex’s mission is to revolutionize the way people and goods are moving around. With its best in class self-driving cars technology, Yandex lets people move from point A to B safely, conveniently, and most efficiently. Our fully autonomous vehicles are built upon the blend of specialized hardware, sensors, and state-of-the-art technologies like computer vision, advanced deep learning, sensor fusion, and human behavior prediction. All these were developed in-house by our top-notch R&D teams comprised of people who face toughest technological challenges every day. If you are as enthusiastic about self-driving cars as we are and like working in an extremely agile, challenging, and rewarding environment, we shall talk.\n\nRequired experience:\nB.Sc. in Computer Science from a leading university;\nfluent in C++ and Python;\nBig Data industrial experience (MapReduce);\nhands-on machine learning experience;\nexcellent writing and communication skills in English.\n\nOptional:\nM.Sc. or Ph.D. in CS/EE/Math or related;\nadvanced machine learning or deep learning skills;\nindustrial experience in machine learning productization;\nexpertise in cloud technologies.\nResponsibilites\nAs a software engineer, you will be responsible for the design and implementation of data- and compute-intensive pipelines for machine learning tasks. You will invent and experiment daily building upon Yandex’s cloud and big data technologies as well as industry-leading tools and frameworks. You will collaborate with the international team of scientists, engineers, and product managers.','2020-07-10',254),(166,'Software Engineer, Product','Facebook\'s mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. Through our family of apps and services, we\'re building a different kind of company that connects billions of people around the world, gives them ways to share what matters most to them, and helps bring people closer together. Whether we\'re creating new products or helping a small business expand its reach, people at Facebook are builders at heart. Our global teams are constantly iterating, solving problems, and working together to empower people around the world to build community and connect in meaningful ways. Together, we can help people build stronger communities - we\'re just getting started.Our Tel Aviv Engineering team is developing products across all of Facebook stack. As an engineer in our team you will work on products that affect the lives of billions using a variety of technologies including large scale systems, big data problems and complex networking technologies. We are looking for full stack engineers who are able to move quickly between technology stacks. If you\'re experienced with various technologies, a fast learner and have a get things done mentality, we\'d love to hear from you!\n\nResponsibilities:\n\nIdentify issues and implement solutions to complex problems in large scale backend infrastructure and mobile platforms\nAnalyze & solve difficult problems across the stack\nWork closely with operations and infrastructure to build high scale backend services\nMininum Qualifications:\n\n5+ years of previous work experience or B.Sc. or M.Sc. in Computer Science or related field\nProficiency in either Python, Ruby, PHP/Hack, C/C++, Java, C#, go, nodejs etc.\nExperience on full stack development (Server + web or Server + mobile)\nKnowledge of low level networking or OS internals (Linux, iOS and Android infra) would be useful\nPreferred Qualifications:','2020-07-03',127),(167,'Software Developer for The Editor Server','Wix’s Backend Editor team, where lead developers shape the architecture of our backend microservices. We work on some of the most important and critical services at Wix, developing and maintaining highly scalable systems that support Wix’s 160+ million users—and the people who visit their websites. Our development culture is transparent, highly technical, and agile. Because we ship often, we’ve adopted continuous delivery and test-driven development (TDD). We code for JVM, mostly in Scala and also for Node.js.\n\nWe’re also mentors, helping less-experienced engineers improve and hone their skills so that they can eventually be tech leads themselves. We strive to hire bright engineers who have ‘fire and forget’ abilities, and who are independent, innovative, and bold.\n\nYou are:\n\n\nA passionate developer with at least 3 years’ experience in Scala/Java/C++/C','2020-07-21',91),(168,'Software Storage Developer','NVIDIA is looking for a Software Developer who sees the big picture. This essential role will give you an opportunity to craft and deliver a new class of user-space applications and kernel space drivers. You will join the storage software team. The team is in charge of developing storage drivers & storage emulation solutions.\n\nWhat you will do:\nMaintain and enhance NVME Linux Kernel drivers\nEnd-to-end responsibility (Design to unit test) for a major feature in user space and kernel applications\nParticipate in enhancing our cutting edge technology storage solutions\nWork with partners and customers worldwide\nEnsure that modules and/or product(s) across your teams are consistent\nDrive performance tuning, usability improvements, and test automation\nWays to stand out from the crowd:\nB.Sc. in Computer Science\nExperience in c/c++ language\n2 years working experience or more as c/c++ software engineer – Advantage\nExperience in storage (mainly NVME protocol) – Huge advantage\nExperience in RDMA – Huge advantage\nSelf and quick learning abilities\nExcellent social and written communication skills\nExcel working in a dynamic, highly interactive environment\nNVIDIA is widely considered to be one of the technology world’s most desirable employers. We have some of the most forward-thinking and hardworking people in the world working for us. If you\'re creative and autonomous, we want to hear from you!\n\nNVIDIA is committed to fostering a diverse work environment and proud to be an equal opportunity employer. As we highly value diversity in our current and future employees, we do not discriminate (including in our hiring and promotion practices) on the basis of race, religion, color, national origin, gender, gender expression, sexual orientation, age, marital status, veteran status, disability status or any other characteristic protected by law.','2020-07-17',257),(169,'Embedded Software Engineer','Join the Amazon family and take part in the development of next generation products that will define the future of the cloud domain.\n\nAnnapurna Labs, an Amazon company, is looking for talented engineers to help us develop cutting edge products within disruptive system architecture. Youll have the opportunity to work on the technologies that power the worlds largest Cloud provider, within a dynamic, open, and fast-paced environment.\n\nTo learn more about Annapurna you\'re welcome to watch the following videos from the recent re:Invent conference:\nhttps://youtu.be/o9_4uGvbvnk?t=15m59s\nhttps://youtu.be/dfEcd3zqPOA?t=38m49s\nhttps://youtu.be/LabltEXk0VQ?t=20m1s\n\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Bachelors Degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering\n· 4+ years professional experience in software development\n· Strong knowledge in C\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Deep understanding of computer architecture\n· Experience with low level SW and the interaction with HW devices\n· Hands-on experience working with embedded systems\n· Experience with SoC development life cycle\n· Experience working in Linux environments\n· Experience working with networking protocols\n· Personal characteristics: Team player, highly motivated and committed, passionate about SW development, willing to work in a dynamic and demanding environment and a fast learner\n· Amazon is an Equal Opportunity-Affirmative Action Employer Minority / Female / Disability / Veteran / Gender Identity / Sexual Orientation','2020-07-16',115),(170,'Software Engineer, Infrastructure','Facebook\'s mission is to give people the power to build community and bring the world closer together. T