al orientation, pregnancy or maternity leave status, race or national or ethnic origin, age, religion or belief, gender identity or re-assignment, marital or civil partnership status, protected veteran status (if applicable) or any other characteristic protected by law. AstraZeneca only employs individuals with the right to work in the country where the role is advertised.','2020-07-03',316),(223,'Payment Approval Representative','As a global, multi-national company, we would like to ask that you please submit your resume in English.\n\nHave we got a job for you?!\n\nPayment Approval Representative, Petach Tikva\n\nBuild Your Career | Have Fun | Make a Difference\n\nIf you\'re the kind of person that loves to get stuff done, collaborate with colleagues all over the world and is interested in joining a fast growing global company that is trusted by the world\'s top digital brands and truly cares for its customers, join us at Payoneer!\nCheck out our values\n\nIf you are looking for an opportunity to enter the Fintech world, we are looking for a team member to join our Payments Approval Department.\n\nWhat will you do...\nMonitor all incoming and outgoing payments to our Account holders\nInvestigate source of funds\nApply sound decision making, balancing the approval/decline of payments and services with compliance and risk considerations\nDetect suspicious or fraudulent behavior patterns by using sophisticated in-house built monitoring systems\nContact end users and report to internal and external providers while maintaining operational SLAs\nHave you done this kind of stuff?\n1-2 years experience in the world of online payments\nMother Tongue level English - writing, reading and speaking\nAbility to cope with changing requirements and different regulations per area/financial flow\nHands-on and team player\nStrong analytical and critical thinking skills\nAbility to make timely decisions, at times despite ambiguous processes or guidelines\nFlexible hours (working across the globe)\nDegree in Business Management, Economics or a related field (not a must)\n\n\nThe following would be considered a plus for candidates:\nExperience in the world of online payments\\ risk\\ compliance\nAdditional languages: Chinese\n**This is a full time hourly based salary position**\n\nA few words about us\n\nPayoneer is a leading payment platform and one of the world\'s fastest growing fintech companies, ranking high on Inc. 5000, Deloitte Fast 500, and the CNBC Disruptor List. We empower entrepreneurs and businesses anywhere in the world – from Cairo to California, Buenos Aires to Bangalore and Tel Aviv to Tokyo – to go beyond and grow successful, sustainable businesses. With millions of customers in over 200 countries worldwide and trusted by clients like Amazon, Airbnb and Google, Payoneer truly connects anyone, anywhere, with opportunities to trade globally.','2020-07-08',321),(224,'General NI Potential Candidate','Haven\'t found the job your looking for?\nWere always looking for more talent!\nSubmit your resume here','2020-07-26',160),(226,'Commission Analyst','Commission Analyst\n\nSummary\n\nVaronis Systems is the leader in unstructured and semi-structured data governance software, which is any human generated data that is within a company’s environment. Our goal is to protect companies most sensitive information from insider threats and cyberattacks. We do this by allowing organizations to analyze, secure, manage, and migrate their volumes of unstructured data.\n\nKey Responsibilities\nPreparing the commission plans to each of the Company’s Sales Team\nAnalyzing the cost of commission per Sales group, and ensuring no deviations from the budgeted target\nCommunicating and addressing any questions and quarries Sales team have in relation to their compensation\nReviewing the commission expense per team, per territory and ensuring no unusual events took place\nIn charge of updating the plans in the Company’s billing system so all information is accurate and up to date\nDesired Skills & Experience\nBachelor’s degree.\nWilling to work hard under pressure in a global dynamic environment\nOutstanding oral and written communication skills is a must\nSuperior planning, organization, and problem-solving skills\nHighly responsible, very detailed oriented and organized (Attention to details, follow-up, and time management skills)\nExcellent relationship building and people skills\nFluent in English (writing and speaking) and in Hebrew\nTeam player, can-do attitude, flexible, self-motivated\nMotivated, eager to learn','2020-07-16',324),(227,'Account Manager - Publishers','Woobi is searching for a talented, passionate for games, sales oriented Publisher Account Manager to join our team!\n\nIn this role, you will be the day to day contact with our publishers, and the voice and face of our business. Publisher Account Manager is responsible for growing each account, running trend and analytical reports, managing all post-sales communication with the publisher, from onboarding and testing, regular check-ins and relationship development, to monthly reporting.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nWorking with the publisher development team to onboard new publishers.\nWork with the ad operations team for campaign alignment.\nManage direct publisher accounts, monitor daily, and actively look for opportunities to grow supply by partnering with the sales team.\nTroubleshooting issues that arise with publisher integrations.\nBuild a long lasting relationship with each publisher.\nOnboard, train, and make recommendations to publishers integrating Woobi\'s monetization platform\nAssist with the integration of all new SDK publishers and ensure their needs are answered quickly and accurately by facilitating solutions across multiple departments\nHave regular meetings and calls with key publishers to ensure elite level service and to anticipate any development changes or needs\n\nRequirements:\nEnglish at mother tongue level – a must. Additional language is an advantage\nKnowledge / Experience in the online advertising industry – a must\n1-2 years experience as a Publisher AM – an advantage\nPrevious programmatic RTB experience - High Advantage\nSales experience - an advantage\nAnalytical skill and attention to detail – a must\nAbility to provide a high quality of customer service to Publishers.\nProficiency in MS-Office applications (Word, Excel)\nStrong written and oral communication skills\nBasic technical abilities, comfortable with learning new platforms, quick learner\nFunction well in a fast pacing environment, able to work under pressure\nEnthusiastic, highly motivated individual with a serious work ethic\nProactive; able to work independently; tenacious; goal-oriented; team player\nMultitasking skills, ability to see a project through until the end\nVery well organized\nBachelor\'s degree - an advantage','2020-07-11',325),(228,'Didn\'t find a position that suits you? Send us your Resume!','In case you haven\'t found any other relevant openings that suits your skills, please attach your CV here.','2020-07-21',17),(229,'Product Analyst','A profitable startup with over 25000 paying customers worldwide developing a platform for project management is looking for a Product Analyst to ensure data and insights are actionable to drive decisions across the business and communicate data-driven insights and recommendations to key stakeholders at all levels. The offices are in Tel Aviv.\n\nדרישות משרה\n3 years of experience in a similar data analyst role.\nProficiency level of SQL.\nמיומנויות ויתרונות\nGreat storyteller and communicator, and can build relationships with a diverse set of stakeholders.\nDeep understanding of numbers, as well as a strong business sense.\nCapable of tackling ambiguous problem spaces and challenges\nPassion for making sense of user behavior, using any available methods and a dedicated advocate of a user-centered approach in product development\nCurious, independent and rigorous\nTechnical competence to perform advanced analytics with large datasets with technologies such as Python, Pandas, R, SQL.','2020-07-27',166),(230,'Sales Operations','For more than 11 years, Amazon Web Services (AWS) has been the worlds most comprehensive and broadly adopted cloud platform. AWS offers over 100 fully featured services to power the infrastructure of millions of active customers, including the world\'s fastest growing and most successful startups. Startups are a critically important and growing subset of customers with unique needs, priorities, and growth trajectories that distinguish them from traditional businesses and require different engagement strategies and sales motions from sellers to effectively acquire, grow, and retain them long-term on the AWS platform.\n\nTo drive our sales strategy with Startup customers in Israel we are seeking a Sales Strategy and Operation (SSOE) Leader for the Startup business. This role will partner with the Startup Sales Leader for Israel to serve as their strategic adviser and will drive execution against our priorities with startup customers. The position is a part of our wider SSOE team covering all of the AWS Startup business in EMEA.\n\nThe startup team and startup customers are among the most exciting, diverse, and dynamic at AWS and we are looking for an adaptable and experienced senior leader to raise the bar of this team. In addition to a strategic advisory role, the position will hold the Startup team in Israel to a high standard by managing all rhythm of the business activities such as Monthly Business Reviews, Quarterly Business Reviews, and other cadenced reporting and metrics. The position will assist in evaluating and forecasting attainment against revenue and goals, owns field compensation topics, utilizes CRM tools to derive well-vetted analysis, and supports other ad-hoc requests and analysis as needed.\n\nThis is a hands-on position - the ideal candidate must be willing to roll up the sleeves as well as plan and execute on long-term strategic horizons. This position will support on day-to-day execution of the business including commission and quota plans, managing account moves, staffing operations, etc. This role must earn trust through performance and relationship building, think strategically and analytically about business challenges, and have experience in program management and an analytic background.\n\nKey responsibilities include, but are not limited to:\n• Serve as strategic adviser to the leader of Israel Startup business\n• Lead the local planning process and run the operational cadence of activities including regular business reviews, Offsite strategy workshops, target planning, account/territory planning\n• Provide insights via external market research and deep dives, and work backwards from the needs of specific customer segments to define strategic initiatives and develop KPIs to track progress.\n• Manage operational aspects including revenue tracking and forecasting, program management, compensation, sales performance evaluation, and reporting.\n• Define team and individual goals and objectives to support the overarching organizational mission and strategy.\n• Prepare ad hoc analysis & participate on projects as needed.\n\n\n\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n• Experience in a role in Operations Analytics or Sales Management\n• Ability to conduct sophisticated and creative analysis of complex data and translate the results into actionable deliverables, messages, and presentations\n• Experience in multi-functional domains including compensation, forecasting, territory planning, opportunity management, and organizational development.\n• Demonstrated ability to define, refine and implement sales processes, procedures and policies\n• Strong proficiency with Microsoft Office Suite required (extensive knowledge of Excel required)\n• Excellent cross group collaboration skills.\n• Bachelors degree is required\n• Fluent in English and Hebrew\n\n\n\n\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n• Experience within a high-growth, technology company\n• MBA or other advanced degree\n• Highly organized, have multi-tasking skills, and efficient in ambiguous situations.\n• Deep expertise and familiarity with cloud computing products, services and sales strategies.\n• Track record of due diligence across business and customer segments, leading to creation of new customer sales programs to drive growth.\n• Able to operate successfully in a rapidly changing and ambiguous environment.\n• Able to operate successfully in a lean, fast-paced organization, and to create a vision and organization that can scale quickly.','2020-07-07',115),(231,'CUSTOMER SUCCESS MANAGER','General Description\n\nManagement of customer portfolios and ongoing business development\nManage online campaigns and monitor performance\nOptimize campaigns based on data and yield reports\n\nWhat you will need\n\nA Relevant B.A/BS.C/LLB Degree such as – Economics, Business, Law, Accounting, Behavioral Science\nGreat interpersonal skills\nStrong analytical skills\nCreativity and ability to think “outside the box”\nAbility to multi-task in fast-paced environment\nSales orientation\nFluency in English- mother-tongue or very strong written and verbal skills\n\nWould be great if you have\n\nPrior experience in client management/ account management/Sales and business development (In English)\nStrong Excel skills\nBasic knowledge in various tech languages\nAdditional languages','2020-07-06',329),(233,'Content Writer & Community Engagement Manager (Native English Speaker) - Part-time (10:00 - 15:00)','* Part-time position (10:00 - 15:00 / Flexible ) *\n\nThe affiliaXe team is looking for a passionate & results driven Content Writer & Community Engagement Manager to create engaging content and oversee our social & email marketing efforts.\n\nThis is an exciting opportunity to join a fast-growing marketing company and to apply your writing, emailing and community engagement expertise.\n\nPosition Responsibilities:\nManage the company\'s social activities (LinkedIn, Facebook, Twitter & Instagram)\nCreate engaging email campaigns to keep the community active\nImplementing and testing new ideas to build engagement: email communication campaigns, social media competitions, incentive programs, etc\nCreate original content with focus on SEO, results & user engagement\nWrite high quality reviews for products, websites and services\nProduce & Publish educational knowledge (wikis/educational text and/or videos) for our users, clients and staff\nWork closely with Web Designers, Developers & Freelance Content Writers\nRequired Skills:\nNative level of English, since you will be mostly working with markets from all over the world\nMust be passionate about marketing, technology & social networking\nMust have a clear experience with community engagement and email marketing\nHigh level written and communication skills, effective usage of persuasive language and development of themes/brand voice\nExperience with online marketing, email marketing, social media, SEO, Analytics tools, etc\nFamiliar with community engagement and email marketing related KPIs and used to working with regular reporting\nCopywriting experience for web / email campaigns\nExperience in inbound/outbound marketing\nFluency in Microsoft Windows-based desktop applications: Word, PowerPoint, Excel\nGood organizational skills, open-minded, flexible and proactive\nAt least one year of experience of working in a similar position\n* Part-time position','2020-07-28',331),(237,'Researcher','DRW is a technology-driven, diversified principal trading firm. We trade our own capital at our own risk, across a broad range of asset classes, instruments and strategies, in financial markets around the world. As the markets have evolved over the past 25 years, so has DRW – maximizing opportunities to include real estate, cryptoassets and venture capital. With over 1,000 employees at our Chicago headquarters and offices around the world, we work together to solve complex problems, challenge consensus and deliver meaningful results. It is a place of high expectations, deep curiosity and thoughtful collaboration.\n\nDRW is looking for highly skilled Ph.D. level researchers for an Algorithmic Trading Research Group in Tel Aviv. DRW Israel\'s office is located in Alon Towers. DRW offers highly competitive compensation packages.\n\nOur formula for success is to hire exceptional people, encourage their ideas and reward their results with competitive compensation packages.\n\nResearchers at DRW apply tools from a variety of disciplines including statistics, control theory, machine learning, optimization, and signal processing to develop algorithmic trading strategies. Our research team collaborates on idea generation and strategy development, while encouraging independent exploration and original approaches. Researchers have access to clean data integrated with a high performance computing grid and the support of dedicated software developers.\n\nJob Description\nDevelop algorithmic trading strategies and improve existing strategies\nIdentify inefficiencies in the financial markets and characterize them with mathematical models\nPredict price movements using statistics, signal processing and machine learning\nApply optimization techniques to construct optimal portfolios\nDesign automated trading agents that achieve efficient execution\nDirect software developers in the translation of the research into production software\nRequirements\nA Ph.D. with a focus on machine learning, signal processing, optimization, control or statistics\nAn interest in financial markets\nExperience in handling large data sets using languages such as Python, R, MATLAB, or C++\nSignificant hands-on experience with formulating a research problem, conducting the research and developing a working system\nExcellent communication skills\nPrior experience in finance is not necessary; finance-specific training will 