ence working for a consumer Internet company.\nAbout us: We are headquartered in San Francisco, with R&D in Tel Aviv, and are backed by Sequoia, GreatPoint Ventures, Optum Ventures, and large BCBS payers. Our customers include health plans and physician-led healthcare systems.\n\nBy inputting your information and clicking \"Submit Application\", you acknowledge that you have read and agree to Vim\'s Candidate Privacy Notice.','2020-07-27',105),(247,'Senior Security Researcher','SentinelOne is shaping the future of endpoint security through its unified, converged platform that automatically prevents, detects, and responds to threats in real-time. Our unique approach is based on deep inspection of all system processes combined with innovative machine learning to quickly isolate malicious behaviors, protecting devices against advanced, targeted threats in real time.\n\nWhat are we looking for?\n\nWe are looking for talented security researchers, people who look at the world differently, who explore, \"hunt\", live to beat the system and challenge it. People who are in a pursuit to outsmart the malware and overcome it.\n\nWhy us?\n\nBecause you will meet extraordinary challenges facing the newest malwares and tech obstacles and overcoming them.\nYou will work with the very BEST in the industry in a flexible and independent environment.\nYou will influence the design of a disruptive product that will shape the security industry of tomorrow.\n\nWhat will you do?\n\nYou will be responsible for strategic long term research, that would involve deep researching of OS internals including Windows and Linux, research for new vulnerabilities and novel threats.\nYou will be developing and using internal research tools, evaluating new advanced technologies and discovering new ways to detect/prevent attacks.\nYou will also be encouraged to write white papers, blogs and articles.\n\nWhat experience or knowledge should you bring?\nDeep understanding of Windows Internals knowledge - understanding how core system components (Process and Threads, Virtual Memory and more) work behind the scenes.\nExperience in malware analysis (statically and dynamically) and reverse engineering (x86/x64).\nExperienced with analysis tools, such as: IDA, WinDBG, SysInternals and more.\nExperienced with Python, C and C++ programming.\nExperienced with vulnerability research and/or vulnerability exploitation - advantage.\nUnderstanding of existing AVs internals - advantage.\n#LI-AR1','2020-07-19',78),(248,'Big Data Tech Lead','Big Data Tech Lead- IL\n\nWe\'re looking for an experienced Big Data Tech Lead, with a HO attitude to build our next generation scalable big data processing and analytics systems in the cloud. We work with various Big Data technologies such as Spark, Kafka, Druid and ElasticSearch (and more), and were looking for you...\n\nExperience and Skills:\n2+ years experience in technical Leadership for Enterprise products- mainly in a startup environment.\nEnthusiastic about performant web scale & complex systems and flows\nMeticulous about scalability and security\nExperienced in planning and building scalable real-time data systems\nHO Experienced in Java- mandatory.\nWell founded in data-structures and analytical problem solving\nTeam player and ability to mentor\nA fast learner with a \"Can DO!\" attitude\nEven Better:\nExperience in building microservice based architecture\nExpertise with Amazon Web Services ecosystem\nExperience in Complex processing workloads with SPARK.\nExperience with ElasticSearch or other search engine technologies\nHO Experienced in Kotlin/Scala or similar\nFamiliarity with building microservices using Akka, Vert.x or similar\nB.Sc. or M.Sc. in Computer Science / Engineering / Bioinformatics, or equivalent\nKnowledge with DynamoDB, Cassandra, MongoDB or other NoSQL databases\nSelf-taught from Coursera, Khan Academy, edX or others\nWhy Totango?\nTotango is a fast growing start-up building an ambitious cloud application. Youll 