se group students from all three degree-granting campuses (NYU New York, NYU Abu Dhabi and NYU Shanghai).\n\nThis is a part-time/fixed term role providing operational support to the site’s academic and student-life departments (classes, trips, events, delegation visits, etc.). Administrative support and coordination with internal and external stakeholders, suppliers and service providers. Procurement, invoices, payment processing.\n\nQualifications:\nBA degree is required (students pursuing a BA can also apply)\nExperience in administrative management – Advantage.\nFluency in both English and Hebrew are required; knowledge of Arabic is an advantage.\nExcellent skills in Microsoft Excel.\nFamiliarity with Israeli and American cultures.\n\nAdditional Information:\nThe University is an equal opportunity employer committed to equity, diversity and social inclusion.','2020-07-10',348),(251,'Copywriter and Storyteller','Description\n\nOverwolf is seeking a talented copywriter to join our pack - a wordsmith with passion for content writing and storytelling.\n\nOverwolf is a platform for developers who want to integrate with PC games. Thousands of developers use Overwolf to build mods and apps for leading PC games such as League of Legends, Fortnite, CS: GO, Hearthstone and many more.\n\nThis is a great opportunity to join a professional and fun marketing team at Overwolf and work in the dynamic esports and gaming ecosystem.\nResponsibilities\nWrite copy and micro-copy for a variety of products, including Overwolf’s home page, app interface, landing pages, video scripts, technical API documentation, blog posts and social media posts\nCraft stories and press releases that follow the brand’s tone of voice, working with our PR agencies in Israel and LA\nHelp other departments in the company to sharpen their copy so it’s clear and consistent\nCreate buzzworthy / viral content based on brand needs and partner opportunities\nDevelop and maintain a clear and consistent brand message in all copy\nRequirements\nNative English speaker\nMust be a PC gamer, bonus points if you play League of Legends\n2+ years of experience writing marketing/advertising copy and micro-copy\nExperience in a fast-growing startup - an advantage\nExperience in the video game industry - a strong advantage\nBachelor’s Degree (B.A./B.S.) in advertising, marketing, creative writing, communications, or a related field\nExcellent and communication skills (verbal and written)\nStrong interpersonal skills and a can-do approach\nJob Types: Full-time, Part-time, Contract\n\nExperience:\nCopywriting: 1 year (Preferred)\nLanguage:\nNative English (Required)','2020-07-26',349),(252,'Web Search Evaluator','Appen Web Search Evaluators perform basic online tasks to evaluate the quality and relevance of internet-based search results, advertisements and/or web page content. This position helps to ensure that people around the world are presented the most effective and relevant data possible when searching for information on the internet. In other words, your input counts in creating a better user experience for people looking for data online around the globe.\n\nThe Web Search Evaluator position is a part-time, work-from-home opportunity where all you need is a computer, sound card with speakers, high-speed internet connection and experience searching for information on the internet to get the job done.\n\nThese are entry-level positions that will allow the Web Search Evaluator to learn new technologies and receive income while helping improve the quality and relevancy of search returns!\n\nDon’t miss this opportunity to be part of Appen’s rapidly growing global Web Search Evaluation services providing critical data for the world’s top internet search engine companies!\n\nWork Schedule:\n\n· The Web Search Evaluator positions are flexible, part-time and up to 4 hours a day - 5 days a week!\n\nRequirements:\n\n· Must be currently residing in and able to perform work tasks in Israel\n\n·