d requirements. Our team will evaluate your application and review all positions that might be a quality fit based on your skills and experience. To see all our work opportunities, please visit join.appen.com.','2020-07-27',23),(253,'Product Manager - Detection','SentinelOne is a pioneer in delivering autonomous security for the endpoint, data center, and cloud environments to help organizations secure their assets with speed and simplicity. SentinelOne unifies prevention, detection, response, remediation, and forensics in a single platform powered by artificial intelligence. With SentinelOne, organizations can detect malicious behavior across multiple vectors, rapidly eliminate threats with the fully-automated integrated response and adapt their defenses against the most advanced cyberattacks.\n\nWhat are we looking for?\n\nWe are looking for a Product Manager, to drive all of our detection engines to new heights, initiate and drive the development of new detection engines and maintain our product position as the leading endpoint security platform in the market. This person must have hands-on experience in the area of security research and in leading visionary products, managing research teams, and experience in transforming advanced research capabilities into a leading product.\n\nWhy us?\n\nBecause you will work in a dynamic, exciting industry (Cyber Security) and will influence the way it shapes tomorrow. You will work tightly with the best endpoint security researchers and responsible for the most advanced endpoint protection product in the world. You will be part of a rapidly growing startup on an amazing journey of success, you will work with great people in an open, fun environment, and you will be part of an organization that truly values its people.\n\nWhat will you do?\nBe a part of a talented team that drives the product.\nUnderstand the market, competition, and customer needs in-depth.\nBe able to discuss the product detection solution with both very technical (like pen-testers) and less-technical personas, customers and prospects.\nGuide new detection capabilities from concept phase to launch by working closely with customers, sales engineers, R&D, and Research teams.\nDefine product phases to allow gradual release at SentinelOne intensive delivery pace.\nBuild and maintain our product detection roadmap and own the process of forming it into a plan for execution.\nEnsure our product detection capabilities are built to meet the most advanced attack simulation frameworks and top market 3rd party certification tests.\nMake data-driven decisions to prioritize the various detection efforts in the organization.\nDefine KPIs for Detection engines and push to have our R&D meet or beat them.\nHelp incubate new research initiatives from early exploration phases into a winning product capability.\nWhat experience or knowledge should you bring?\nYou have 2+ years of experience in product management and in shipping successful Security (especially endpoints) products at scale.\nYou have 4+ years of experience in hands-on security research, preferably in the area of endpoint security.\nYou move fast with a growth mindset. Ready to work hard and under pressure but you don\'t compromise on work ethics\nYou treasure collaboration and brainstorming, improve your team members and you see the product success as your own success.\nYou are technical enough to support yourself and the team around you and at the same time- enthusiastic to do and learn anything.\nKnowledgeable about next-generation endpoint protection, cyber-security technologies (traditional antivirus, network security, firewalls, vulnerability assessment, incident response, forensics)\nKnowledge around common attack flows and the malware world.\nGood understanding of kernel internals, at least in one of Linux, Windows, or macOS operating systems.\nStrong written, verbal, editing and presentation skills.\nHighly collaborative with a deep sense of ownership and accountability.\n#LI-AR1','2020-07-22',78),(254,'Internship Opportunities for Students','With our world being more connected than ever and the rise in cyber threats, Microsoft has placed itself as one of the top security providers in the world. Realizing the opportunities talents in Israel can offer, a great portion of Microsoft’s security business is being run from the Israeli Development Center (or ILDC) with offices in Herzliya, Haifa, Tel-Aviv and Nazareth.\n\nThe teams in Israel are building products to protect cloud environments and on-premise networks, connected devices (IoT) and endpoints. Security administrators can control and manage their data and networks, quickly detect threats and respond using powerful tools for investigation and analytics.\n\nAre you an excellent teammate, looking to work in a live, dynamic environment, where you can contribute, learn and influence? Are you passionate about developing state-of-the-art engineering systems? Then your place is with us!\n**Our team will review applications as of March 1st. Last chance to apply is on May 1st***\nResponsibilities\n\n\nAs the field of cyber security is constantly evolving, we\'re looking for engineers to develop new features and components to help make our products more powerful and up-to-speed with the latest challenges.\n\nYou\'ll be taking part in deploying your code to production and making sure it works up to scale, to support the rising number of customers, onboarding every day.\n\nThis is an opportunity to reach tens of thousands of customers, and develop your logic based on real-life user data, and actual hack attempts.\n\nTo build the best Security tools, we try to think like an attacker on the one hand, and the responding Security Officer on the other.\n\nQualifications\nDue to nature of the Intern Program we are currently prioritizing applications from students with final graduation date of winter 2022 and beyond\nCurrently pursuing bachelor\'s, master\'s, or PhD degree in engineering, com