estration. We solve some of the most complex challenges in security and usability. Our technology enables large enterprises to standardize and simplify their identity infrastructure to accelerate time to market and reduce the cost of new account opening, authentication, authorization, compliance and fraud prevention related initiatives.','2020-07-16',83),(260,'Partner Success Manager','In a nutshell:\nWere looking for an initiative oriented, strategic and proactive Partner Owner to join our growing Partners Team.\n\n\nRequirements:\nMinimum of 5 years experience in an international customer facing role\nEnterprise B2B experience with international clients - Must\nExperience in a role that requires consistently re-closing/up-selling /cross-selling opportunities\nNative English speaker - Must\nTech-savvy with super strong analytical and technical skills\nExperience in project management\nSuperb writing and communication skills\nGreat interpersonal skills\nHighly-motivated team player\nProblem-solver, resourceful and independent\n\n\nFull Description:\nvCita is a simple & effective business management software for small businesses. It includes everything service providers need to manage their business and generate more revenue: client management, online scheduling, payments, promotions, and lead generation widgets.\nOur teams are based out of Bellevue, Washington and Tel-Aviv, Israel.\nThe partners\' team provides technical solutions for our partners, working hands-on with them during the onboarding process and building the relationship. The team manages medium/large size partners, in the USA, Australia, Europe & Israel. As a Partner Owner you are the face of vCita to our big partners abroad. Your goal will be to learn as much as possible about their business and be our in-house expert on their workflows and needs.\nYou\'ll be expected to proactively manage the business through periodic on-site reviews and web conferences. You\'ll be working daily with various teams within vCita, including Product, BI , CS and Development.\n\n\nResponsibilities:\nBe the main focal point of the partner\nIncharge of all communication with the partners going forward, post-sale\nLead new partners onboarding projects to completion. Manage the partner onboarding process, from start to end\nManage product requests by partner\nMaintain the relationship with the partner and make sure the partner keeps on growing\nConduct training and knowledge transfer to partners\nManage expectations - internally and externally, be required to raise flags on time\nRepresent vCitas interests to the partner and the partner interests to vCita\nBuild relationships with key customer contacts to ensure high levels of satisfaction and lay the foundations for continued growth and partnership\n\n\nApply Now!','2020-07-06',358),(261,'Big Data Team Lead','Big Data Team Lead- IL\n\nWe\'re looking for an experienced Big Data Team Lead, with a HO attitude to build our next generation scalable big data processing and analytics systems in the cloud. We work with cutting edge Big Data technologies such as Spark and ElasticSearch to stay ahead, and were looking for you...\n\nExperience and Skills:\n2+ years experience in technical management/ team Leadership for Enterprise products- mainly in a startup environment.\nEnthusiastic about performant web scale & complex systems and flows\nMeticulous about scalability and security\nExperienced in planning and building scalable real-time data systems\nHO Experienced in Java- mandatory.\nWell founded in data-structures and analytical problem solving\nA fast learner with a \"Can DO!\" attitude\nEven Better:\nExperience in building microservice based architecture\nExpertise with Amazon Web Services ecosystem\nExperience in Complex processing workloads with SPARK.\nExperience with ElasticSearch or other search engine technologies\nHO Experienced in Kotlin/Scala or similar\nFamiliarity with building microservices using Akka, Vert.x or similar\nB.Sc. or M.Sc. in Computer Science / Engineering / Bioinformatics, or equivalent\nKnowledge with DynamoDB, Cassandra, MongoDB or other NoSQL databases\nSelf-taught from Coursera, Khan Academy, edX or others\nWhy Totango?\nTotango is a fast growing start-up building an ambitious cloud application. Youll have the opportunity to learn cutting edge technologies and make an impact.\nTotango leads the exciting new field of Customer Success. We help businesses pro-actively support their existing clients and reduce churn.\nWe\'re based in Tel-Aviv near Azrieli and HaShalom train station. It\'s a vibrant and fun place surrounded by public transport and great restaurants.\nYou\'ll enjoy the company of super bright people that are exciting to work with.\nPowered by JazzHR','2020-07-07',13),(262,'Senior DevOps Engineer','Cloudinary is the leading provider of media management solutions, powering the trusted, award-winning visual experiences for many of your favorite brands. Cloudinary is the de facto media platform standard for developers and non-technical brand managers looking to upload, store, transform, manage, and deliver images and videos online. With more than 30 billion assets under our management and 6,500 customers worldwide, were always looking for exceptional people to help us reach for the cloud\nJoin our R&D team as a Senior DevOps Engineer. Define and create operations tools and processes for a massively scalable system, backing 10,000s of the worlds busiest websites and apps, which will hopefully grow to become the media backbone for the whole Internet.\nWe offer a fun and supportive environment in which you will constantly learn and evolve, and where your ideas will be embraced and pursued.\nResponsibilities\nManage live production environments. Handle ongoing monitoring and troubleshoot failures.\nProvide architectural solutions for complex data and processing requirements involving large-scale systems and rapid growth.\nManage live environment from server infrastruc