r community to develop, design and execute the appropriate testing solutions for our customers\' needs.\n\nDrive an effective use of testing resources and activities budget to increase financial efficiencies.\n\nMain point of interaction and/or escalation for all testing related items.\n\nMaintain an active communication with the internal account owners to ensure the customers satisfaction.\n\nSkills & Requirements:\n\nYou hold a degree, preferably in Engineering, Business, or a related field.\n\nAt least two years of experience as a Project Manager, Test Engineer or Test Manager for mobile applications, web products or a SaaS solution.\n\nGood technical and business understanding and a strong interest in the “app and digital world”.\n\nExcellent problem-solving skills, customer orientation, organizational and time-management skills.\n\nProven ability to manage multiple projects simultaneously while maintaining attention to details, timelines and budget.\n\nAbove-average commitment, quick learner and ability to work independently in a dynamic environment.\n\nExcellent written and verbal communication skills in English and Hebrew are a must.\n\nInterested? Apply right now!','2020-07-24',361),(264,'Fraud Analyst','Description\n\n\nTaboola is the world\'s leading content discovery platform, serving 360B recommendations to over 1B unique visitors each month on the web\'s most innovative publisher sites, including NBC, USA Today, The Weather Channel, Tribune and Fox Sports.\n\nTaboola is looking for a top notch Fraud Analyst whose main goal is to investigate low post click trends and improve conversions across our portfolio of brands. In addition, the Fraud analyst will be collaborating with a wide range of teams and stakeholders, and be exposed to various facets of our business, He will define and track fraud metrics, help improve the work process, and prevent fraud. The successful candidate should have a strong analytic background, technically skilled and have business