d organized.\n\n\nAbout The Role:\nManage high budget and large-scale Facebook and Google PPC campaigns\nAnalyze and optimize campaigns constantly to maximize revenue\nInitiate and implement improvements and creative solutions to increase campaigns activity\nRespond quickly to changes in online marketing and adapt to capitalize on new opportunities\n\n\nSocial Title:\nPPC Campaign Manager - Entry Level\n\n\nSocial Description:\nWe\'re ramping up our paid media spend and are looking for an Entry Level PPC Campaign Manage to join our team. This entry level position will help ensure we\'re maximizing our ROI during this time of growth. This is an amazing opportunity to join an incredible team and experience success with one of Israel\'s fastest growing startups.\n\n\nOur Team:\nThe Marketing team is the growth engine of monday.com! With every kind of marketer using every possible offline and online channel, the sky\'s our limit. We are bold, unconventional and on a mission to reach as many potential customers that we can\nAs the user acquisition team, we focus on the no-touch funnel, conquering all things online in our quest to target and reach more people. Were big spenders, with just the right mix of analytical and creative thinking.','2020-07-02',367),(270,'Junior Test and Product Engineer','Challenging job in an innovative environment. A group that will ramp you to the highest standards, with career path and skills that are always desired in the industry. Covering test development of SoC devices from the test concept & methodology phase through the ramp-up of the test solution, both hardware and software, all the way to volume production. Creating test programs and special tests for debug , characterization, and optimization towards mass production. Identifying bugs and design marginalities, leading characterization & debug efforts , production optimization and follow up . Close cooperation with design (e.g. DFT) , hardware and software teams\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Bachelor\'s/Master\'s degree in Electrical Engineering\n· Work effectively in a start-up culture\n· A team player, with the ability to work in a rapidly evolving environment\n· Scripting skills\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Knowledge of SoC testing during both the development and volume production stages, including product ramp-up\n· Experience with Automated Test Equipment (ATE), preferably on Teradyne UltraFlex and Advantest 93k\n· Experience with C or C++ programing\n· Understanding of DFT and DFM methods\n· Familiar with chip design processes\n· Familiar with debug techniques\n· Familiar with data mining and analyses techniques','2020-07-23',115),(272,'Backend Developer- Cloud Team','SentinelOne was founded in 2013 by an elite group of cyber-security and defense experts. In our R&D offices in TLV, we develop a next-gen endpoint and server protection SW product that uses several layers of protection, including behavioral analysis (with ML on the collected data), anti-exploitation, traps and more in order to stop zero-day attacks that other vendors simply cant. It also provides unparalleled threat visibility at a minimum system impact.\n\nWhat are we looking for?\n\nWe are looking for a strong backend technical engineer to take part in building our next generation management console platform as a service.\n\nWhat will you do?\n\nYou will take part in the architecture, design and implementation of a multi-disciplinary cloud native software platform that will serve thousands of users and hundreds millions of events as part of SentinelOne\'s management console region services.\n\nWhat experience or knowledge should you bring?\nA degree in Computer Science/Software engineering from a well-regarded university OR a comparable experience from well renowned companies/military units\nAt least three years of hands-on experience with using object oriented methodologies with Python or Java/C#/C++ or Similar.\nFluency in Linux based operating system with focus on embedding open source tools within commercial products.\nAbility to quickly dive into new products and understand their inner working.\nSelf-driven individual who enjoys a startup culture.\nAdvantages:\nExperience with Dockers, Helm & Kubernetes.\nFamiliarity with AWS and other cloud platforms\nExperience with large scale management systems and performance.\n#LI-AR1','2020-07-14',78),(273,'Product Analyst','You figure out how the user navigates our web applications, find the pain points and help wrinkle them out. Google Analytics and A/B testing tools like Optimizely are some of the toolings you are using to get the data. You know that data does not just fall from the sky (or from a tracking script) so you are tech savvy enough to identify, track, and use the data you need to optimize the user experience. Sounds like you? Find out more!\nYour job:\nTogether with your teammates of the Frontend team in Tel Aviv, you are responsible for the best possible customer journey on our website. You will be part of a cross-functional team consisting of Developers, Quality Assurance Testers, UX/UI designers, a Product Owner and Scrum Master. Using the agile framework, we add new features, improve conversion and innovate our website iteratively. Your contribution to the team is to provide performance insights for newly added features, the overall usability of the website and monitor our KPI\'s with a direct line to the Product Owner.\n\nAt the same time, you are part of the global Web Analytics tribe which is responsible for the alignment and guidelines of our data infrastructure among all Takeaway platforms.\n\nYour tasks consist of:\nDesign measurable metrics and KPIs according to the business of stakeholders, and develop reports using Business Intelligence tools and languages such as Tableau, Amazon Redshift SQL and Python, so that stakeholders can regularly keep track of their achievement and know where they are right now\nYou are able to interpret the questions behind the question and have experience in communicating clearly and in a concise manner with stakeholders\nProactively propose business actions and opportunities which is taken out from data to stakeholders, so that they can take an innovative approach to efficiently and effectively improve their business\nTrain fellow team members on the usage of the various data & analytics tools available\nYou know exactly how data is gathered and processed by the different analyzing tools\nYou are the first point of contact and thought leader for behavioural analysis and website optimization strategies by using Google Analytics, Optimizely X, and similar toolings\nIt would be a plus if you know how to find improvement points and troubleshoot tracking implementations on customer-facing applications.\nYour profile:\nAdvanced knowledge of SQL and Business Intelligence tools especially Tableau, Google Analytics and at least good knowledge of another data analytics tool like R, Python etc\nBeing able to do in-depth analyses, for example, performance analysis about the different steps in the funnel\nYou have at least 5 years working experiences as Web Analyst, Business Analyst, Conversion Optimization Specialist, Product Analyst or similar areas\nYou have been working together with product and different IT departments\nYou know how to assist them with insights from the digital analytics platform and help them optimize their products for web applications\nYou relish working in a team and enjoy collaborating and sharing knowledge with your peers.\nHere\'s our offer:\nThe freedom to go where no one in our company has gone before\nPossibilities to strengthen your skills and grow in the role\nWork in a fast-growing company\nBeing part of a new, young, professional and international team\nAn office location within the heart of Tel Aviv\nInternal as well as external schoolings and conferences\nHackathons and prototyping of new solutions\nAwesome team events!','2020-07-27',99),(274,'Personal Assistant','A