vel: Russian*, French*, Spanish*or Arabic* speaker\nExcellent command on written and spoken English*\nService-oriented, passionate about providing delightful service to our customers\nPositive communication and attitude\nMulti-tasker, fast typing skills\nSelf & Quick learner\nFlexibility and availability to embrace change\nExcellent computer Skills\nExperience in working in a goal-oriented environment\nPrevious customer service experience – advantage\nIs this you? Have you done this before?\n\nCheck us out!\nEver wondered whether that perfect combination really exists? You know, the job we always dream where we develop professionally and enjoy a fun workplace surrounded by passionate people, at a company that is really changing the world?\n\nPayoneer empowers entrepreneurs and businesses anywhere in the world – from Cairo to California, Buenos Aires to Bangalore and Tel Aviv to Tokyo – to expand beyond their borders and grow successful, sustainable businesses. With millions of customers in over 200 countries worldwide, Payoneer connects anyone, regardless of their location or socio-economic background, with opportunities to trade globally.','2020-07-27',321),(287,'Security Analyst - Vigilance - Student position (prior experience in Malware Analysis is a must)','SentinelOne was founded in 2013 by an elite group of cyber-security and defense experts.\nIn our R&D offices in TLV, we develop a next-gen endpoint and server protection SW product that uses several layers of protection, including behavioral analysis (with ML on the collected data), anti-exploitation, traps and more in order to stop zero-day attacks that other vendors simply cant.\nIt also provides unparalleled threat visibility at a minimum system impact.\n\nWhat are we looking for?\nJoin our Vigilance organization, an elite force of cybersecurity experts providing a Managed Detection and Response (MDR) service to our largest customers. Help drive a world class threat monitoring, hunting, and response services. Be an integral part of a 24x7 follow-the-sun global SOC, and work with key POCs, and customers, to provide an additional level of security and confidence, by leveraging intelligence feeds, threat logs, and IOCs. Collaborate with our threat team and researchers, and various RnD teams as you help shape our product, help customers be more secure, and introduce yourself to the cyber tech ecosystem.\n\nWork hours and locations\nInitial (paid) training will take place at SentinelOne TLV\nWork is based on 8-9 Hr shifts either in our TLV office (Sarona Tower, Tel-Aviv), or from home when applicable.\nAbility to fulfil shifts on Friday (daytime), Saturday or Sunday (evening time) at least once a week.\nWhat will you do?\nProactively monitor, and review threats and suspicious events from customers participating in the service\nInvestigate alerts, triage, deep dive, and come up with proper action item and remediation plan\nUse multiple sources of data from the customer, our intelligence cloud, external threat feeds, etc\nPerform proactive hunting for threat data, leveraging our deep visibility abilities, and proprietary research cloud.\nWork with the customer to follow up on items that require additional investigation\nProvide Incident follow up & support\nMaintain excellent customer satisfaction through professional, proactive and personal service\nWork closely with our researches and development teams\nContribute to our knowledge base by creating malware analysis cookbooks, and best practices\nWhat experience or knowledge should you bring?\nStudies towards a Science/Engineering degree or in a relevant topic- Bachelors or Masters\nExperience in IT, Technical Support or SOC operations or IR -a must\nStrong network and security knowledge or certification is desired\nExperience with SQL queries, bash, python and PowerShell is fantastic\nExcellent customer oriented individual, a problem solver\nProfessional and articulate with excellent written communication skills\nAbility to multitask and prioritize\nMulti OS support experience: Windows, Mac & Linux (mobile platforms - an advantage)\nExperience with host base (endpoint agent), or sandbox (network based) security solutions - an advantage\n#LI-AR1','2020-07-06',78),(288,'QA Student','Description\n\nNICE is looking for ambitious QA student to join our Multi-Channel Recording Next Generation group.\n\nThe group plays a substantial role in the development of NICE flagship product suite which builds Enterprise solutions for contact centers.\n\nResponsibilities\n\nYou’ll have the opportunity to be part of a diverse Agile team gaining exposure to cutting edge technologies and real-life product delivery.\n\nYou will work collaboratively with professional engineers, architects, and product managers to create NICE next-generation products.\n\nAs a QA Student, you will participate in the design and planning meetings, design the test plan and execute exploratory testing to cover the areas and scenarios that are not covered by the automation tests. Root cause Analysis for defects found including logs gathering and analysis. Become an expert on the Product and the ways it is used\n\nEducation:\nStudent of a Technological study\n(Computer Science, Computer Engineering, Software Engineering or Industrial Engineering)\nAt least 1-2 years to graduation\nRequirements:\nAvailable for 100 hours / 2.5 days a week\nAbility to create Test Plan Design and Execution of Exploratorily Testing\nExcellent problem solving and analytical skills\nStrong debugging and investigation skills\nOrganized and Methodological approach\nGlobal mindset & written English\nHigh self-learning capabilities and Creative Thinking\nExcellent interpersonal communication skills\nAccountability, Self-driven and independent\nAdvantage:\n- Experience and Knowledge of QA Methodologies\n- UI/Web Testing Experience and debug tools\n- Automation tools : Selenium, Cucumber\\SpecFlow\n- Programming skills, SQL Knowledge\n- Experience with Agile/S