ions.\n• Proven hands-on experience with Juniper, Cisco, F5, Brocade\n• Proven experience with FW, and IPS systems.\n• Linux – hands on experience.\n• English – written and spoken in high level\nAdvantages:\n• Knowledge with Nagios\n• Scripting (Perl/Bash/Python) abilities.\n• Linux/Windows administrator.\n• Terraform\n\nPERSONAL QUALITIES:\n• Excellent communication skills (interpersonal and organization aspects) in English and Hebrew\n• Team player\n• Hunger for technology\n• Service awareness\n• Analytic skills, wide system vision + troubleshooting\n]]>','2020-07-05',217),(290,'ASSISTANT CONTROLLER','We\'re looking for an Assistant Controller to join our global finance team.\nAs a Assistant controller you will be a key part in building finance strategy, processes, reporting and promote Gett\'s international business.\nWe in Gett are having exciting times- the Company did an amazing turnaround to operational profitability in 2019 and we are working towards profitability in all countries and line of businesses in 2020, as well as working on being prepared for an IPO.\nResponsibilities:\nAssist in preparation of the monthly, quarterly and annual closing\nAssist in preparation of the quarterly and annual consolidated financial statements\nAssist in preparation of the statutory financial statements and the tax return report\nAssist with global Bookkeeping and helping with the day-to-day finance operations of Gett subsidiaries\nAssist with analysis as necessary for managerial reporting, forecasting and budgeting\nAssist with the external relationship with auditors\nUndertaking of ad-hoc financial tasks\n\n\nRequirements:\nRequirements:\nCPA from a Big 4 accounting firm, with a minimum of 3-4 years\' of experience\nExperience in the high-tech industry- advantage\nknowledge and experience in IFRS and US-GAAP\nFluency in English (spoken and written) a must!\nOutstanding attention to details and excellent time management skills\nAbility to work in a fast-paced work environ