 .\n● Coordinate meetings, travel needs, schedules, etc.\n● Assist building and execute team social & wellness activities: happy hours, holidays, events and more.\n● Perform other administrative duties and special projects as required.\n\nDesired Skills and Experience:\n\n● Minimum 2 years as an Office Manager in the Hi-Tech industry.\n● Strong organizational and time management skills. Ability to work with a high sense of urgency within established timelines exercising consistent follow-through/follow-up when necessary.\n● Ability to multi-task and operate independently, in an environment of frequently changing priorities.\n● Experience in leading projects in different capacities, end to end.\n● Superb interpersonal and communication skills (verbal, written - Hebrew & English)\n● Ability to maintain discretion and strict confidentiality.\n● Strong computer skills in MS Office/Windows, and demonstrated ability to learn new systems.\n● Quick thinker/learner with a “business owner” mentality who will handle assignments, tasks, and projects with intrepid initiative and ingenuity.\n● Ability to excel in a fast-paced and demanding environment by demonstrating a strong work ethic and dedication to your role.\n● Demonstrates “internal” customer focus and ‘can do’ attitude. Enjoys giving excellent service.\n● Professional appearance and demeanor.\n\nLocation: Tel Aviv, Israel\n\nWhat you\'ll get:\n\nA competitive salary, and equity in a super fast-growing company, taking over commercial insurance\nA strong emphasis on work-life balance\nBeautiful offices in the heart of Tel Aviv, near the train station and main bus stops\nPassionate, smart, and fun people to work with\nYou will never lack a challenge, we are a unique blend of a fast-growing tech startup, an international firm, and an insurance company\n\n\nLearn more at at-bay.com','2020-07-17',397),(292,'Lobby Service Representative - Intel Jerusalem Campus','Job Description\n\nLobby Service Representative, Intel Jerusalem