tioned itself as a Fintech leader, pioneering revolutionary practices such as social trading, blockchain and machine-learning-based investment products. eToro is a regulated and secure platform, operating in full transparency with its clients interest in mind.\nAs Marketing Operations Project Coordinator, youll be responsible for the smooth workflow of a range of marketing projects, including creative 360 campaigns, localizations, video productions, company events, and more. Must thrive in a dynamic, fast-paced, and deadline-driven work environment.\n\n\nRequirements:\nBachelor\'s degree in business, marketing or a related field\nStrong English communication skills\nHighly motivated to learn.\nSelf-starter, proactive and flexible; must be comfortable in a fast-paced environment\nOutstanding project management skills, demonstrated by the ability to coordinate between multiple interfaces.\nHave excellent attention to details\nHighly collaborative team player, comfortable with a dynamic working environment\nExcellent computer skills (specifically MS Office applications)\nTechnical orientation\nOrganized with strong multi-tasking and people skills\nIn addition, you must possess the following qualities:\nHave strong organizational and communication skills along with the ability to prioritize under pressure\nBe self-motivated and proactive\nHave the ability to work cross-functionally and manage cross-department projects\nHave an excellent attention for details\nHave verbal and written communication skills\nThis position is a full-time position\nEntry level position and is suitable for newly graduated candidates','2020-07-13',339),(294,'Performance Marketing Analyst','As a Performance Marketing Analyst on the SodaStream Direct to Consumer team you\'ll be making a direct impact on the growth of the online platforms. Your main responsibility is to generate actionable insights that lead to improvement of core KPIs. You will also be responsible for hypothesizing and testing, optimizing and reporting. This role is well suited for those who are analytically strong and want to see tangible impact of their work.\n\nWhat You\'ll Do\nHelp optimize user acquisition campaigns primarily with paid social platforms: Facebook/Instagram, Snapchat, and Adwords.\nMonitor, optimize, and report performance of campaigns on an ongoing basis.\nHypothesize and test for creative optimization.\nIdentify key audiences and provide creative solutions based on data to improve campaign performance.\nWork closely with campaign managers to understand and optimize the full funnel.\nUtilize your understanding of attribution and tracking measurement platforms (ie. Google analytics) to analyze for data accuracy and attribution.\n\nDescription Of Duties\nExecute reporting / analysis against the analytics needs of internal marketing teams to enable data-driven marketing and drive efficiencies through developing automated reporting/dashboards, maintaining related systems, developing new processes, and implementing testing\nUse analytical and database skills to develop reports and analyses to assist in decision making processes\nDelivers recommendations and consultation to business teams regarding the efficiency of a variety of marketing tactics\nTake input from team leadership and business owners to understand the goals of the business and define meaningful metrics to track those goals\nDevelop executive level materials on marketing insights and learnings\nMaintain existing suite of automated reports.\nPerform ad-hoc analyses to answer business questions or generate data sets.\n\n\nRequirements:\nWho You Are & What You\'ve Done\nAt least 3 years of professional experience in a data-driven position\nGood understanding of Online Marketing Channels (Display, SEM, etc) and KPIs (CPO, ROI, CVR, etc)\nUnderstanding of attribution and the basic assumption behind various attribution models\nExperience with various data tools (Google Analytics, Adjust, Atlas, Google Adwords and Facebook Reporting) a strong advantage\nExcellent knowledge of Excel and Google Sheets including Google Sheet Scripts and VBA\nKnowledge of programming language like Python and SQL a plus\nAbility to generate insights from large amounts of data, evaluate validity and present insight concisely to relevant stakeholders\nAbility to manage complex projects across departments (including technical and non-technical colleagues)\nHands on and pragmatic approach to new challenges (ability to Google)\nData Driven Background\nFluency in English\n\n\nCountry:\nIsrael','2020-07-12',400),(295,'Junior FP&A analyst','Junior FP&A analyst\n\nSummary\n\nVaronis Systems is the leader in unstructured and semi-structured data governance software, which is any human generated data that is within a company’s environment. Our goal is to protect companies most sensitive information from insider threats and cyber-attacks. We do this by allowing organizations to analyze, secure, manage, and migrate their volumes of unstructured data.\n\nResponsibilities\nAnalyze business and financial trends of the company\nPrepare insightful ongoing management reports to support their decision making\nAd-hoc in-depth analysis on business performance to c-level management\nParticipate in preparation of quarterly financial statements\nPrepare quarterly presentations to board of directors\nQA testing of BI reports and dashboards\nRequirements\nBachelor\'s Degree in Economics (from universities)\nStrong analytical skills with highest standards of accuracy and precision\nAbility to think creatively, highly-driven and self-motivated\nAdvanced Microsoft Excel experience\nSuperior planning, organization, and problem-solving skills\nExcellent verbal and written communication skills\nStrong English (writing and speaking)\nExperience with Python, Power Query, Power Pivot, Power BI - Advantage','2020-07-15',324),(296,'Customer Success Representative','A leading Financial Technologies start-up is looking for a Customer Success Representative!\nIn this role you will be in charge of inside sales, validating leads, customer support, analyst relations, and internal company processes.\nPart of your job will involve working with multiple systems such as databases, payment services, and you will work with most of the teams in the company.\nThe target is to grow sales while ensuring excellent service standards, respond efficiently to customer inquiries and maintain high customer satisfaction.\nResponsibilities\nInside Sales\nSupport\n\nExternal Communications:\nData Validation\n\nדרישות:\nAbility to multi-task, prioritize, and manage time effectively\nHigh school degree\nLanguage skills\nEnglish- high level (read and write)\nOther languages- advantage\n\nאיזור: גוש דן\n\nתחום: Success Customers','2020-07-15',155),(297,'Head of HR – Temporary position (Replacement for maternity leave)','Description\n\nWho Are We?\n\nMoovit (www.moovit.com), an Intel company, is a leading Mobility as a Service (MaaS) solutions company and the maker of the world’s #1 urban mobility app. Moovit was acquired by Intel in May 2020 to join forces with Mobileye and advance its MaaS strategy. Together, Moovit and Mobileye will accelerate the global adoption of autonomous transportation.\n\nMoovit’s iOS, Android, and Web apps guide people in getting around town effectively and conveniently, using any mode of transport. Introduced in 2012 it now serves over 800 million users in more than 3,200 cities across 103 countries.\n\nMoovit amasses up to six billion anonymous data points a day to add to the world’s largest repository of transit and urban mobility data. For governments, cities, transit agencies, and private companies, Moovit offers AI-powered MaaS solutions covering planning, operations, and optimization with proven value in reducing congestion, growing ridership, and increasing efficiency and asset utilization. Industry leaders such as Microsoft, Uber, and Cubic have partnered with Moovit to power their mobility offerings.\n\nMoovit is looking for a *maternity leave replacement* for the Head of HR position.\n\nWe are looking for a strong, flexible, creative, results-oriented HR professional. In this role, you will be managing an amazing HR team and be responsible for:\nOversee, lead and execute the Human Resources agenda\nLead day-to-day HR processes, practices and initiatives, including coaching leaders and managers, building winning teams, managing performance, employee engagement and more.\nBe a trusted advisor to employees and managers and support their day to day activities. Use your overall interactions with people to obtain an ongoing holistic understanding of organizational pulse and provide insights accordingly.\nTake an active part in maintaining the unique culture and guiding Moovit employees in it.\n\nRequirements\n\n10+ years of experience in Human Resources fields, as a HRBP or HR Manager in a fast-growing high-tech company\nAbility to thrive in a fast paced environment with multiple priorities that contains massive hiring\nExperience managing HR teams\nExperience leading and developing professionals in a combination of General HR, Talent Acquisition, OD, comp&ben in a global environment.\nStrong consultation skills, including the ability to challenge and impact senior stakeholders\nA creative, resourceful problem solver, excellent teamwork skills, proactive and self-motivated.\nAbility to work effectively with all levels of the organization and with a wide range of personalities and skill sets.\nExcellent English - Must.','2020-07-28',403),(302,'Warehouse Operative','Cosentino Group is a global, Spanish, family-owned company that produces and distributes high value innovative surfaces for the world of design and architecture. As a leading company, it innovates and anticipates, together with its clients and partners, solutions that offer design and value, and inspire the life of many people. This goal is made possible by pioneering leading brands in their respec