veral efforts simultaneously (multitasking)\nAbility to work effectively in a team oriented environment\nWhy should you join Philips?\n\nWorking at Philips is more than a job. It’s a calling to create a healthier society through meaningful work, focused on improving 3 billion lives a year by delivering innovative solutions across the health continuum. Our people experience a variety of unexpected moments when their lives and careers come together in meaningful ways. Learn more by watching this video.\n\nTo find out more about what it’s like working for Philips at a personal level, visit the Working at Philips page on our career website, where you can read stories from our employee blog. Once there,you can also learn about our recruitment process, or find answers to some of the frequently asked questions.\n\n#LI-EU\n\nContact\n\n\nIf you forgot your password, you can click the Forgot Password button on the Sign In screen to reset it.\n\nIf you have any other questions regarding the recruitment process please refer to our FAQs. In case of technical difficulties with the website, please send an email to careersite@philips.com.\n(Note: To ensure fairness and legal compliance in our recruitment processes, only technical issues will be monitored through the above inbox. Please do not submit resumes or applications to this email, as they will not be reviewed. Only applications received through the online application process will be considered.)','2020-07-02',417),(319,'Operational Excellence Tech Leader','Drive operation of Annapurna products in the fleet, to achieve excellent customer experience, and high standard of operations by integrating technical domains and aligning their operation with customer expectations, enhancing product metrics, monitoring their operation and executing on tasks & processes.\nDeep dive to set in motion actions and drive them for both short term resolution and long term remediation over different domains and stages of the product life cycle (e.g. IC design, screening, board design, FW, etc.).\nWork with peers across AWS (e.g. EC2, EBS, HWEng, NETEng, etc) and at Annapurna on health improvements, metrics definition, issue resolutions and other aspects of fleet operation.\nDrive resolutions, high standards of operational excellence, and improve on execution.\n\n\nDuties include:\n· Continuously enhance and improve the operational health of Annapurna products, either directly or by raising the bar of monitoring, debugging and reporting of product issues in the fleet\n· Integrate knowledge and data from customers and data sources for fast resolution of issues\n· Co-work with Annapurna Labs monitoring team and root cause team to improve quality and reliability of products operation in the fleet\n· Drive cross-functional tasks and follow-up on their execution to closure\n· Define and drive methodologies, flows and infrastructure for product operational excellence in the fleet\n· Drive and maintain trainings, quality documentation and collateral in order to improve in-fleet operations\n·\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· 10+ years experience in a technical position working on complex products\n· 7+ years technical managing of programs\n· Proven ability to deliver results in a matrix organization\n· Independent and biased for action\n· Multi-tasking and methodical\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Experience with Datacenter products, Networking, Servers, HW/SW integration, OS/Drivers integration\n· Experience in operations and process of large scale infrastructure\n· Good verbal and written communication in English','2020-07-10',115),(320,'Application Engineering Leader - Cisco Silicon One™','What You\'ll Do\n\nYou will be working as part of the Silicon One™ team, leading and shaping the team responsible for our Customer Product Support. interacting with our customers and Cisco products groups, both on software and hardware aspects, support developing, based on next generation silicon architectures, the tomorrow\'s leading network infrastructure solutions.\n\nManage and lead this new domain of implementation and integration, support activities with various of the most exiting next generation products systems, developed around Silicon One™ unique solution. The team you will be leading, and yourself, will provide integration and product support, troubleshoot, debug and resolve the issues, and provide actionable data to our internal team, SW and HW.\n\nAs part of this role, you will be working closely and be facing both with internal engineering, SW and HW, and with the customer products SW team, to guide them throughout their system development.\n\nLead the strong product specialist and customer facing team, and responsible for the entire support activities.\nAnalyze and debug next generation Network Infrastructure systems products with their technical issues and inquiries.\nProvide and be the centric guidance and support for Silicon One™ engineering teams.\nHands-on diagnose and troubleshooting, working on networking protocols for switch/router and infrastructure products.\nWork closely with Cisco and other customers System product development teams, understanding the applications the data path required and help them by bridging the knowledge on the various aspects related\nEstablish a new domain of Silicon One™ customer interface processes\nMange and build up with our customers, hands-on debug skills and methodologies\nTransform specialized knowledge of our development methodology and state of the art architectures to our System Product engineering teams.\n\nWho We Are\n\nLeaba semiconductor was acquired by Cisco a few years ago. and now Silicon One™ is the center of Cisco’s SW and ASIC design.\n\nYou\'ll be part of our Group driving our game changing next generation network devices - Cisco Silicon One™. Our unique team works in a startup atmosphere inside a stable and leading corporate.\n\nOur R&D center and development principals are very unique, hosting all silicon HW and SW development disciplines inside under our group.\n\nWe are transforming the industry and building a new internet for the 5G era, providing a unified, programmable silicon architecture that is the foundation of all Cisco\'s and other Network future routing products.\n\nOur devices are designed to be universally adaptable across service providers and web-scale markets, designed for fixed and modular platforms. Our devices deliver high speed without sacrificing programmability, buffering, power efficiency, scale or feature flexibility.\n\nCisco Silicon One™ is a revolutionary, ground-breaking technology for our customers and end users for decades to come! The Internet now has a new faster, better, safer engine!\n\nLearn more about us right here:\nhttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/solutions/service-provider/innovation/silicon-one.html\n\nhttps://fortune.com/2019/12/11/cisco-ceo-chuck-robbins-chips/?_lrsc=ce750ac5-11c8-4995-bfd3-936de1c06009&dtid=osolin001080\n\nhttps://www.calcalist.co.il/internet/articles/0,7340,L-3775619,00.html\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iy8259BGg6U\n\nWho You Are\n\nExperienced Application Engineer for software and hardware development and integration.\nExperience in leading and manage local and multi-geographic team\nFamiliar and have some background level in networking, topologies and forwarding protocols (bridge and routers)\nReady to learn and expand your knowledge in the top line domain next generation Network infrastructure products\nA real team player with positive attitude and strong communication skills\nStrong orientation for system wise testing and debugging, a problem solver\nGood Knowledge on latest programming languages (Python,Perl).\nBackground in Software/Electrical Engineering\n\nWhy Cisco\n\nWe connect everything: people, processes, data, and things. We innovate everywhere, taking bold risks to shape the technologies that give us smart cities, connected cars, and handheld hospitals. And we do it in style with unique personali