th Senior Specialists and Practice Experts\nBe a part of a leading company, globally recognized as a Visionary by Gartner Magic Quadrant\nAs a global company, we offer unique placement opportunities around the world\nIntrigued to find more about us?\nVisit our website at www.qualitestgroup.com\nCheck out our Career page: http://qa-jobs.qualitestgroup.com/','2020-07-17',412),(369,'Linux Kernel SW Engineer','Join the Amazon family and take part in the development of next generation products that will define the future of the cloud domain.\n\nAnnapurnaLabs, an Amazon company, is looking for talented engineers to help us develop the semiconductor platform which is based on revolutionary architecture.\nYoure invited to take part in developing, integrating and deploying cutting-edge networking technologies. Starting from the identification and definition of project requirements, feature development and deployment, to operational support on a very large scale.\n\nThis role has hands-on Linux kernel development. Your code will run on millions of servers worldwide as part of the nitro system - few software engineers in the world have a similar opportunity to create code that runs at such a scale - not only at Amazon, but in the software industry as a whole. as part of your role you will develop new kernel drivers and improvements, support existing drivers, you will submit your code to upstream Linux kernel maintainers, and follow open source best practices.\n\n\nTo learn more about Annapurna you\'re welcome to watch the following videos from the recent re:Invent conference:\n\nhttps://youtu.be/o9_4uGvbvnk?t=15m59s\nhttps://youtu.be/dfEcd3zqPOA?t=38m49s\nhttps://youtu.be/LabltEXk0VQ?t=20m1s\n\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Bachelors Degree in Computer Science or Electrical Engineering\n· 3+ years of experience with embedded SW development\n· Knowledge and good understanding of HW, SW and the entire System view\n· Specific in depth knowledge of the use, design, and development of Linux operating system internals, including the kernel is required for this role.\n\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Experience with SoC development life cycle\n· Experience working in Linux environments\n· Experience working with storage and networking protocols\n· Personal characteristics: Team player, highly motivated, willing to work in dynamic and demanding environment and Fast learner\n\nAmazon is an Equal Opportunity-Affirmative Action Employer Minority / Female / Disability / Veteran / Gender Identity / Sexual Orientation','2020-07-24',115),(370,'Logic Design DSP Engineer - Cisco Silicon One™','What You\'ll Do\n\nYou\'ll be joining the Front End Design team at Leaba (now part of Cisco) which is responsible for all chip design process from definition/micro architecture to product.\n\nSpecifically you will be dealing with DSP portions of the design and high speed interfaces.\n\nOur front end engineers are dealing with all chip design aspect: Definition, Design, Verification, signoff, validation.\n\nWe use the latest silicon technologies and processes to build largest scale and most complex devices at the edge of feasibility.\n\nWho You\'ll Work With\nLeaba semiconductor was acquired by Cisco a few years ago. It is now the center of Cisco’s ASIC design group.\n\nYou\'ll be part of our Group driving our game changing next generation network devices - Cisco Silicon One™. Our unique team works in a startup atmosphere inside a stable and leading corporate\n\nOur design center is very unique - hosting all silicon HW and SW development disciplines inside one site.\n\nWe are transforming the industry and building a new internet for the 5G era, providing a unified, programmable silicon architecture that is the foundation of all Cisco\'s future routing products.\n\nOur devices are designed to be universally adaptable across service providers and web-scale markets, designed for fixed and modular platforms. Our devices deliver high speed without sacrificing programmability, buffering, power efficiency, scale or feature flexibility.\n\nCisco Silicon One™ is a revolutionary, ground-breaking technology for our customers and end users for decades to come! The Internet now has a new faster, better, safer engine!\n\nLearn more about us right here:\nhttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/solutions/service-provider/innovation/silicon-one.html\n\nhttps://fortune.com/2019/12/11/cisco-ceo-chuck-robbins-chips/?_lrsc=ce750ac5-11c8-4995-bfd3-936de1c06009&dtid=osolin001080\n\nhttps://www.calcalist.co.il/internet/articles/0,7340,L-3775619,00.html\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iy8259BGg6U\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BNkiprGWw4Y\n\nWho You Are\n\n• Logic Design Engineer with up to 5 years’ experience in front end design.\n\n•B.Sc/M.Sc in EE from one of the top universities in Israel with GPA above 85 .\n\n•Experience in DSP – advantage.\n\n•Knowledge in Ethernet mac/phy or other high speed interfaces development – advantage.\n\n\nWhy Cisco\n#WeAreCisco, where each person is unique, but we bring our talents to work as a team and make a difference. Here’s how we do it.\n\nWe embrace digital, and help our customers implement change in their digital businesses. Some may think we’re “old” (30 years strong!) and only about hardware, but we’re also a software company. And a security company. A blockchain company. An AI/Machine Learning company. We even invented an intuitive network that adapts, predicts, learns and protects. No other company can do what we do – you can’t put us in a box!\n\nBut “Digital Transformation” is an empty buzz phrase without a culture that allows for innovation, creativity, and yes, even failure (if you learn from it.)\n\nDay to day, we focus on the give and take. We give our best, we give our egos a break and we give of ourselves (because giving back is built into our DNA.) We take accountability, we take bold steps, and we take difference to heart. Because without diversity of thought and a commitment to equality for all, there is no moving forward.\n\nSo, you have colorful hair? Don’t care. Tattoos? Show off your ink. Like polka dots? That’s cool. Pop culture geek? Many of us are. Passion for technology and world changing? Be you, with us!\n\n#WeAreCisco\n\n#LI-MZ1','2020-07-26',229),(371,'Quality Engineer','Job Description Summary\nCAPA Coordinator\nJob Description\nCAPA Coordinator\nPrimary Work Location\nISR CME-Israel\nAdditional Locations\nWork Shift','2020-07-03',491),(372,'Regional Director','IL-Haifa\nC2.716\n\nDescription\n\nWe are looking for Regional Director that will lead the Countries under his responsibility to profit and excellence, guiding the Country Management teams to achieve best performance. Responsible for business development of the Countries, maximizing Countries\' P&L, initiate value-added services, as well as geographical development. support countries and drive target achievement\nEscalation level for Regional functions/BU vs. Countries pain points, in order to assure smooth business processes. Support Countries as the Company\'s senior representative with customers, suppliers, Head Office, etc.\nCountries\' performance\nEstablish Countries development plan to promote and implement ZIM strategy in relevant countries\nDevelop & promote new growth engines such as shipping and shipping related activities in relevant countries\n3rd party and JV agencies – identify and Negotiate Agreements, aiming to maximize, ZIM share of profit and ensure optimal business representation of ZIM in various countries\nDrive countries to maximize customer profitability including develop relevant KPIs\nCoordinate countriesannual workplan\nGuiding & coaching Country Managers to improve performance and meet targets.\nServing as ZIM\'s senior representative to support Countries with key customers/vendors/potential partners, etc.\nBusiness Development\nExecute initiatives of new business opportunities - including new markets, growth areas, trends, customers, products and services toget