ts via a service call system.\n\nQualifications\n\nSeeking for an experienced and hardworking student with good technical approach, handy man, to provide quality and reliable support to building facilities in Haifa Campus.\nStudent currently pursuing a B.A/M.A or PE degree\nWith at least 2 years until graduation\nPrior experience in Mechanical and/or Electrical systems\nAbility to work independently and be a team player\nService attitude\nHigh level of Hebrew and English\nRelevant educational qualification in Electricity would be an added advantage\nAvailability to work 3 shifts a week (morning/ evening/ night)\n\nInside this Business Group\n\nAs the world\'s largest chip manufacturer, Intel strives to make every facet of semiconductor manufacturing state-of-the-art -- from semiconductor process development and manufacturing, through yield improvement to packaging, final test and optimization, and world class Supply Chain and facilities support. Employees in the Technology and Manufacturing Group are part of a worldwide network of design, development, manufacturing, and assembly/test facilities, all focused on utilizing the power of Moore’s Law to bring smart, connected devices to every person on Earth\n\nILInternJR0129188Haifa','2020-07-27',422),(377,'Network Application Architect - Cisco Silicon One™','What You\'ll Do?\n\nYou’ll live on the seam line between the SW and HW data path architectures of tomorrow\'s leading infrastructure solutions.\n\nLearn the functions, features and roadmap of various Cisco products enabled by Leaba Silicon, and program the device to enable those functions.\n\nContribute to data path architectures of roadmap devices to enable and improve support for new and existing product features.\n\nThis is a unique opportunity to understand products from the high level application down to the data path imaplementation, with diverse career path to SW or ASIC architecture & development\n\nIn this role, you will:\nDesign, develop and program data-path flows to support Cisco infrastructure products\nInteract with Cisco product teams, learn the applications the data path required to support\nDrive the SW/HW integration\ncontribute to the next generation of leading infrastructure products\nWho You\'ll Work With:\n\nYou\'ll be part of our Group driving our game changing next generation network devices - Cisco Silicon One™. Our unique team works in a startup atmosphere inside a stable and leading corporate.\n\nOur R&D center is very unique - hosting all silicon SW and HW development disciplines inside one site. You will work and interact with Cisco product, software and hardware teams as part of your data-path implementation.\n\nWe are transforming the industry and building a new internet for the 5G era, providing a unified, programmable silicon architecture that is the foundation of all Cisco\'s future routing products.\n\nOur devices are designed to be universally adaptable across service providers and web-scale markets, designed for fixed and modular platforms. Our devices deliver high speed without sacrificing programmability, buffering, power efficiency, scale or feature flexibility.\n\nCisco Silicon One™ is a revolutionary, ground-breaking technology for our customers and end users for decades to come! The Internet now has a new faster, better, safer engine!\n\nLearn more about us right here:\nhttps://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/solutions/service-provider/innovation/silicon-one.html\n\nhttps://fortune.com/2019/12/11/cisco-ceo-chuck-robbins-chips/?_lrsc=ce750ac5-11c8-4995-bfd3-936de1c06009&dtid=osolin001080\n\nhttps://www.calcalist.co.il/internet/articles/0,7340,L-3775619,00.html\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=iy8259BGg6U\n\nhttps://www.youtube.com/watch?v=BNkiprGWw4Y\n\nWho You Are?\n\nWe are looking for someone to join a small, and yet influencing team that is:\nFamiliar and have some background level in networking, topologies and forwarding protocols (bridge and routers)\nIs a team player with positive attitude\nEnjoy learning, self learning which can quickly ramp into new domains\nbackground in software/electrical engineer\nHave a B.Sc or higher, cum laude, from the top University’s, or are highly praised/recommended by a Cisco employee.\nWhy Cisco?\n\nAs Cisco, we connect everything: people, processes, data, and things. We innovate everywhere, taking bold risks to shape the technologies that give us smart cities, connected cars, and handheld hospitals. And we do it in style with unique personalities who aren’t afraid to change the way the world works, lives, plays and learns.\n\nWe are thought leaders, tech geeks, pop culture aficionados, and we even have a few purple haired rock stars. We celebrate the creativity and diversity that fuels our innovation. We are dreamers and we are doers.\n\nBe You With Us! #We Are Cisco.\n\n#LI-MZ1','2020-07-23',229),(378,'Senior Software Engineer','Job Title\nSenior Software Engineer\nJob Description\nYou are a part of\n\nPhilips Oncology Informatics is an innovative group within the Philips Healthcare IT division. Our objective is to define and implement the next generation Oncology Informatics end-to-end solutions to enable clinical decision support for all the different clinical disciplines within the oncology treatment pathway.\nIn this role, you have the opportunity to\nbe involved in developing challenging software modules within complex and advanced environment.\n\nYou are responsible for\nResponsible for the design, implementation, integration and testing - implement full-stack application and technologies to assist power Oncology Informatics user experiences\nComply and align with software development professionalism standards within the team (processes and methodologies, quality of requirements, design, coding and testing).\nWrite clean, high quality, solid, readable code that scales.\nDefine functional requirements based on product definitions.\nPromote trust, openness and leverage external capabilities locally and global