s. Join us in working at a local and friendly\nsite with global impact and reach.\n\nA Day in the Life\n\nAs a highly qualified Site\nPrograms Manager we offer you a position where you will work closely with our site\nleadership team. From day one, you will have an immediate impact on our\nproductivity, streamlining strategic initiatives, overseeing cross site programs,\nmanaging key site functions and communicating between departments. Be a\nkey partner in our success.\n\nAs part of your day to\nday you will:\nJob Responsibilities\nOrganize and coordinate site staff\nfunctions and activities\nCoordinate strategic site\ninitiatives and guide to completion\nSupervise daily operations\nand help oversee projects of high importance\nAct as a main consultant to\nthe site leadership for site wide topics\nManage site calendar and\nensure proper planning and deadlines are being met\nWork with and/or lead\ncross-functional teams to simplify and escalate\nBe a liaison for staff,\ndepartment leaders, country initiatives and external partners\nAssist site leader with\ninternal communication and attending to staff needs, ensuring any problems are\nresolved\nKeep leadership abreast on\ncurrent company climate (employee wellbeing, project statuses, new proposals,\netc.)\nManage key administrative and\nfunctional areas (purchasing, admin, travel, metrics)\nBuild strong relationships\nwith employees and oversee their progress, noting any issues or successes\nHelp coordinate business-wide\nprocedures and work to improve existing processes for maximum clarity,\nefficiency, and success\nResearches and recommends new\nand revised policies and strategies\nCreates and maintains systems\nand processes to streamlineoperations\n\nMust Have\n\n• Bachelor’s degree in Business Management or related field\nMinimum of 7 years of relevant programs\nmanagement and operational experience\n• 5 years’ experience in a leadership/management role\nExcellent written and verbal\nabilities in Hebrew and English\nHighly experienced with\nproject coordinating and management\nExcellent oral and written\ncommunication skills\nStrong interpersonal skills\nand a knack for productive collaboration across varying departments\nDetail-oriented and\ndata-driven\nAble to successfully\norganize, lead and direct teams of people\nPossess an encouraging,\ncan-do attitude\nEffective manager\nImpeccable time management\nand multi-tasking skills\nBusiness-minded and a\nstrategic planner\nProven problem solver who can\nmake clear-headed decisions while under pressure\nAbility to analyze and\ncompile large sets of data and present effective reports\nSelf-motivated and\nself-sufficient\nProven creative thinker with\nstrong business acuity\nNice to Have\nMBA preferred\nExperience in global multi-national\norganizations\nYour\nAnswer\n\nIs this the position you were waiting for? Then\nplease apply directly via the apply button!\n\nAbout Medtronic\n\nMazor Robotics, Ltd., a\nMedtronic company .\nTogether, we can change healthcare worldwide. At Medtronic, we push the limits\nof what technology, therapies and\nservices can do to help alleviate pain, restore health and extend life.\n\nWe challenge ourselves\nand each other to make tomorrow better than yesterday. It is what makes this an\nexciting and rewarding place to be.\n\nWe want to accelerate\nand advance our ability to create meaningful innovations - but we will only\nsucceed with the right people on our team.\n\nLet’s work together to\naddress universal healthcare needs and improve patients’ lives.Help us shape\nthe\nfuture.\n\nWhatever your specialty or ambitions, you\ncan make a difference at Medtronic - both in the lives of others and your\ncareer. Join us in our commitment to take healthcare Further, Together.','2020-07-21',509),(387,'System Product Quality & Reliability (Q&R) Practical Engineer','Annapurna Labs is a semiconductor company established by semiconductor industry veterans and is now part of Amazon Web Services. We are developing leading edge products, manufactured on leading edge technologies. We offer a dynamic, open, teamwork environment operating at high pace mode.\n\n\nPrimary responsibilities:\n· Executing product quality & reliability (Q&R) validation and ongoing Q&R monitoring activities and tasks\n· Executing dedicated Q&R experiments and tasks for product development, production test coverage analysis, failure reproduction and analysis, etc.\n· Performing various product testing and inspection tasks for RMAs, product manufacturing quality assessments, supplier and component quality assessments, etc.\n· Selection, purchasing and maintenance of lab equipment and tools\n· Additional responsibilities and challenges are always available based on candidate abilities\n\nBasic Qualifications\n\n· Practical Engineer degree in electrical engineering or computer science or related fields\n· Knowledge of computer architecture, computer networks and data processing\n· Three to five years of relevant work experience\n· Fluent technical writing in English\n\n\n\n\nPreferred Qualifications\n\n· Knowledge and experience in quality and reliability engineering and statistics fundamentals\n· Knowledge and experience in PCBA design, manufacturing, testing and failure analysis','2020-07-08',115),(388,'Product Analyst Student for Advanced Analytics','Job Description\n\nWho are we?\n\nAdvanced Analytics is a leading group at Intel that develops big data, machine learning, and artificial intelligence solutions.\nThe group provides end-to-end solutions internally to Intel worldwide, supporting various divisions e.g.: R&D, manufacturing, sales and marketing etc., as well as products delivered externally, to Intel customers.\nAs a product analyst student you will collaborate with our data scientists, product managers, UX experts and developers in the team, and support the project throughout its life-cycle.\nYou will conduct requirements analysis write requirements & user stories, plan, document and perform the product acceptance testing.\nThe product development is driven by agile software development practices including SCRUM, continuous deployment, and more.\n\nQualifications\n\nWhat are we looking for?\n\n* First or second year student currently pursuing a Bachelor of Science degree majoring in Industrial Engineering or Information System Engineering\nStudents in advanced degrees with experience in Data Mining, Text Mining, Predictive Analytics - an advantage\nCapacity to work 2 - 2.5 days a week in parallel to the studies\nExcellent analytical skills\nMature and independent Highly and self-motivated\nWilling to work on multiple number of tasks in parallel\nExcellent communication skills and a strong team player\nExcellent English communication skills\n\nInside this Business Group','2020-07-06',398);
